title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine all ingredients in plastic container.
Freeze until solid.
Take out of freezer at least 1/2 hour before serving. Return any unused portion to freezer.
It can be kept for at least 2 weeks.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: kentucky chili
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and onion.
Drain and set aside. In kettle, combine tomato juice, water, chili beans, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir in beef mixture; simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti; drain and stir into chili.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mix the ingredients together and put into a large, greased baking dish.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes or until set.

title: savory chicken squares(makes 4)
directions: Chopped chicken can be cooked in the microwave for about 4 to 6 minutes or until done.
Mix cream cheese and 1 tablespoon butter; beat until fluffy.
Add onion, milk, pepper, salt and chicken.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 cup of mixture in center of 2 rolls pinched together at perforations.
Bring corners up together and twist.
Paste each square with reserved butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and oil together.
Blend both sugars, then eggs. Sift flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar together.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place small balls of dough on greased cookie sheet, flattening them with the bottom of small glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: oreo cookies
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Mix pulp, soda, sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add egg, sifted flour and spices.
Drop from spoon and bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Check.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and add enough peppers to taste.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: quick fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 8-inch dish at 350°.
Mix together in bowl the flour, sugar and milk. Place fruit in dish with melted butter. If using canned fruit, pour off most of juice.
Pour mixture over the fruit and butter.
Do not stir. Cook until brown.

title: poppy seed loaves
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in mixer and beat well.
Add water and poppy seed; mix well.
Bake at 325° until toothpick comes out clean (approximately 40 to 60 minutes).
Makes 2 loaf pans or 4 small pans, only fill half full with mixture.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature, then mix cream cheese with condensed milk and lemon juice.
Beat until smooth. Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with favorite fruit pie filling and chill.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Heat peanut butter and butter until melted.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla until blended.
Add flour mixture and stir until combined. Spread batter into prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Makes 3 dozen 1 1/2 x 2-inch bars.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil.
Heat oil to 360°.
Pour batter in funnel and put in spiral shape in hot oil.
Fry about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Serve with powdered sugar.

title: mexican fruit cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add rest. Then add pecans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp bake
directions: In oiled baking dish, spread rice evenly.
Top with shrimp, mushrooms and cheese.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings and pour over shrimp-rice mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buttermilk prune cake
directions: Blend sugar with oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Blend in buttermilk, the nuts and prunes. Bake in a greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: brendan's special drink
directions: Wash and peel carrots and apple.
Cut into small pieces.
Put through juicer.
A yummy and nutritious drink!

title: tialla
directions: Coarsely crumble bread into 1/2-inch pieces; set aside. Combine cheese, garlic powder, basil, oregano and parsley.

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Brown beef with onion; remove from heat and drain excess fat. Add rice to meat mixture and mix well.
Place cabbage in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread meat-rice mixture on cabbage.
Blend soup, water and catsup; pour over meat-rice layer.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve with sour cream.

title: ranch-style hash
directions: In a large, non-stick skillet, brown ground beef over medium heat.
Drain.
Add tomatoes, bell pepper, onion, rice, basil, salt and pepper.
Mix gently but well.
Cover reduce heat to simmer, and continue cooking until rice is cooked and most of the liquid is absorbed.
Garnish each serving with a slice of cheese, if desired.

title: okra dill pickles
directions: Wash and trim okra.
Fill hot pint jars firmly with whole okra, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Place 1 garlic clove in each jar.
Combine salt, dill seed, hot peppers, water and vinegar in large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour hot pickling solution over okra, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Remove air bubbles.
Wipe jar rims.
Adjust lids.
Process pints for 10 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Makes 8 or 9 pint jars.

title: christmas fruitcake cookies(makes a lot!)
directions: Mix first six ingredients, in order, beating in one at a time. Dice pineapple, cherries and dates; flour well.
(Can be done the night before.)
Mix fruit with batter, then add preserves and pecans.
Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheets and bake at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 160 cookies.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Blend oil, sugar and egg yolks; add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add lemon flavoring and last fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.	Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbecue limas
directions: Brown bacon in small skillet.
Add to other ingredients.
Bake in casserole for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In an electric skillet or heavy, wide saucepan, heat 1 1/2 to 2-inches of vegetable oil to 360° on deep fry thermometer.
In a medium bowl, beat egg with milk.
Stir in flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and the cinnamon.
Mix until smooth, holding finger under funnel with 1/3-inch opening.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel.
Starting in center of skillet, drop batter into hot oil.
Move funnel in circle to make snail.
Fry cake, turning once, until golden brown. Lift cake from oil and let drain over skillet.
Place on paper towel and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large cooking pan, saute onions in butter until onion is tender.
Add potatoes, chicken broth and water.
Bring to a boil. Cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Puree half of mixture in blender or with mixer.
Return to saucepan.
In skillet, brown the sausage.
Drain.
Add sausage and milk to soup.
Cook over low heat until sausage is heated thoroughly.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium mixing bowl until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla. Place vanilla wafer in each paper-lined muffin cup.
Spoon cream cheese mix in cups filling full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Leave in muffin pans and refrigerate overnight.
Top with pie filling, preserves or whipped cream.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Toss with mayonnaise just before serving.

title: bacon and potato casserole
directions: Layer casserole with uncooked bacon.
Add cubed, uncooked potatoes.
(Optional, add green peppers and onion.)
Layer cubed Velveeta cheese.
Top with a layer of pepperoni.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: golden ham pie
directions: Saute green peppers and onion in margarine.
Add flour and lemon juice.
Add milk, soup and chopped ham.
Boil for 1 minute. Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put biscuits on top and bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: cake cookies
directions: Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecued brisket of beef
directions: Put meat into a large saucepot.
Cover with water.
Add the onion, bay leaf, cloves and garlic.
Cover and simmer 4 hours or until tender.
Cool in liquid and drain.
Trim off excess fat. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Cut meat across the grain into very thin slices.
Place meat slices on edge in a large, shallow pan.
Pour a mixture of the remaining ingredients over the meat.
Heat in oven at 350° for about 40 minutes, basting occasionally with sauce mixture.

title: peaches and cream cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch pie pan.
Make a batter using flour, pudding mix, butter, egg and milk; beat well. Pour into prepared pan.
Arrange drained peaches over batter, leaving about 1-inch margin of batter around edge of pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, reserved peach syrup and sugar.
Spoon this over the peach slices, still allowing the 1-inch margin of batter.
Sprinkle top of cobbler with sugar-cinnamon mixture. Bake for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: 3-layered dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, oleo and pecans; spread on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven about 15 minutes or until well done and crisp.
Cool.

title: red beans and rice
directions: put the red beans in the pot with the 2 cups of hot water. Put it in the urin on 500 heat.
Put 1/2 c of oil in the pot whil it is cooking.
Cut up 2 onions and put the onions in the suaches in the pot and let it cook for hafe an hour.

title: strawberry pineapple punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ginger ale. Chill until ready to serve. Add ginger ale before serving.

title: christmas polka dot rice(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes. Bake at 450° for 45 to 55 minutes or microwave.
Fry beef and onion and drain. Cut a slice from top of each potato and scoop out inside.
Mash thoroughly.
Add meat, butter and onion to mashed potatoes.
Whip up.
Pile into potato shells.
Top with cheese.
Reheat to melt cheese.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend in a blender the sugar, dry mustard and salt.
Add vinegar then slowly pour in oil a little at a time until mixture thickens.
Add celery seed and onion.
Refrigerate.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: peanut butter bread fingers
directions: Cream together peanut butter and milk; add salt and pepper, then add slightly beaten egg.
Remove crusts from bread slices and cut into narrow strips.
Dip in the mixture and saute in butter.

title: egg noodles with tuna fish
directions: Cook noodles 9 to 12 minutes.
Separate tuna into flakes, mix with soup, milk and seasonings.
Combine egg noodles and mixture in baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Add bouillon and flour.
Add milk and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cream cheese and mushroom soup and stir until cheese melts.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and add to sauce.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: believe it or not cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in your mixing bowl and mix until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonful on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven and cool on cookie sheet until firm.
Remove to racks to finish cooling.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all but rice with fork.
Mix 2 cups cold milk and 4 tablespoons cornstarch.
Dissolve.
Boil, stirring constantly. Mix all ingredients together.
Beat served at room temperature. Does keep but not well.

title: fiesta grilled peppers
directions: Quarter peppers.
Remove seeds and membranes.
Brush the skin side of each pepper with oil.
Place peppers on the grill rack over medium-hot coals.
Grill about 10 minutes or until peppers are crisp-tender and charred.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dove feast
directions: Cut up meat and coat in a mixture of flour, ginger, salt and pepper.
Brown on all sides in hot oil.
Put browned meat in a large covered casserole dish.
Add 3/4 cup hot water.
Cover and put in 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: chocolate cherry creams
directions: Stir chocolate chips and evaporated milk in heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted. Take off heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.
Roll teaspoons of mixture in coconut.
Chill 4 hours.
Keep chilled.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: banana cherry nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and mix.
Then add bananas and mix thoroughly.
Blend in flour and soda.
Add cherries, juice and nuts and stir until mixed.
Pour in 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side up, in a buttered or foil lined pan. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Arrange mushrooms over chicken. Sprinkle small amount of onion mix on top.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve with noodles or rice.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over 10-quarts of popcorn.

title: hot cranberry cider
directions: In large, non-reactive pot or crock-pot, combine all ingredients, except apples.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce to low and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove spices.

title: holiday delight candy
directions: Cook sugar, cream and syrup to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and begin beating immediately.
It will begin to thicken and change color.
Add vanilla, candied fruit and nuts.
Mixture will be thick and sticky.
Pack into a waxed paper lined loaf pan. Press down firmly with a wet spoon.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
After a few hours it will become firm and almost white in color.
Slice after 24 hours and cut each slice into finger lengths.
It will keep soft for several months.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble bacon.
Cook remaining ingredients until thick.
Pour hot mixture over grated cabbage. Add salt to taste.
Add bacon on top.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put ingredients in a 5-quart pan.
Cover and cook until carrots are done (1 hour).
Season with salt, pepper and parsley flakes.

title: spiced fruit compote
directions: Drain fruit, reserving all liquid in a saucepan.
Set fruit aside.
Mix brown sugar, cornstarch, curry powder and dry mustard with reserved liquid until well-blended.
Stir in prunes and apricots.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture boils and thickens.
Add drained fruit.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until mixture is just heated through.
Serve immediately; garnish with peanuts, if desired.
Makes 4 servings each with 162 calories, less than 1 g. fat and 0 mg. cholesterol.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Fold ingredients through mayonnaise and chill to blend flavors.
Serve with hot fish or with meat.
Also good with fish salads.
Makes 1 1/4 cups of sauce.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, put in covered bowl and refrigerate.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all together.
Store in airtight container.

title: taco-nacho dip
directions: On a pizza tray, layer ingredients, beginning with mixture of refried beans and ground beef.
Follow with each of the subsequent ingredients, ending with salsa.
Heat in oven until warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: blotkaka(whipped cream cake)
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions. Cool.
Cut sponge cake in half horizontally.

Using only 1/2, cut this horizontally again. Place one slice on a plate. Sprinkle with pineapple juice and then spread half of the pudding before adding second slice of cake. Repeat the same as first layer. Whip the whipping cream and add the drained, crushed pineapple. Frost cake with this on sides and top.
You may then cover with a Marzipan Topping.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix first 4 things together.
Add any of the other fruits of your choice.
Mix together.
Place into a wax paper lined loaf pan and place into the freezer.
Keep frozen.
Can keep a year in the freezer.

title: creole peppers
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; set aside.
Add cut up peppers, celery and onion to bacon drippings.
Slowly saute until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add tomatoes, hot pepper, salt and pepper. Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Blend corn meal with a little water; stir into simmering mixture.
Cover and simmer another 5 minutes. Crumble bacon on top at serving time.

title: french fried eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant and cut up like large French fries.
Dip in batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle with salt or Parmesan cheese.
Mix flour with salt.
Combine egg, milk and oil. Add to flour mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Best when all ingredients for batter are just put in blender for 1 minute.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Saute onions in butter until golden.
Add catsup, sugar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and seasonings.
Simmer 30 minutes. Add browned hamburger. Simmer 15 minutes longer.
Serve on buns.

title: cheesy green beans
directions: Cook beans and onion in chicken broth until onion is tender. Drain.
Cut 1/8 to 1/4 pound Velveeta cheese in cubes and stir into hot beans.
Let sit for a few minutes while cheese melts. Stir before serving.

title: bean cakes
directions: Mix pinto beans, meal, flour, salt and pepper together. Add a little of each flour and meal until it is thick enough to make patties. Fry until golden brown. Enjoy. They are delicious.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Best if made the day before.
Keeps for 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: mustard dip
directions: Soak mustard in vinegar overnight.
Run through colander to remove lumps.
Cook on stove at low heat with sugar and eggs until thick.
Cool completely and stir in sour cream.
Refrigerate. Great with veggies, cheeses, pretzels and such.

title: cream pie crust
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 9-inch pie dish, pat to spread.
Poke with a fork in a few places.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool before filling.

title: chewy fruitcake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix baking mix and sugar; cut in margarine thoroughly.
Press mixture with floured hands in ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over baked layer. Layer candied fruit and dates over coconut.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over fruit.
Drizzle milk over top.
Bake until light golden brown, 25 to 30 minutes; cool completely.
Cut into bars.

title: chocolate nut loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in chocolate.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Mix in vanilla and 1 cup nuts.
Pour into 5 greased and floured 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake for about 50 minutes, or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: jim's potato casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer potatoes, then green pepper and onion.
Repeat until all ingredients are used up. (Usually 3 layers of each ingredient.)
Season each potato layer with cracked black pepper and Beau Monde (Spice Island Co.), to taste.
Top with butter pads.
Bake covered at 350° for 60 to 75 minutes or until done.
Serves 4.
A good dish to serve with pork.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Peel zucchini and slice.
Dip each slice in beaten egg with 1 tablespoon water.
Then dip in seasoned bread crumbs and fry in oil until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: quick chopped herring appetizer
directions: Combine herring, juice from jar, white vinegar and sugar.
Add onion, apple, green pepper, 1 slice bread and eggs.
If mixture is too loose, add second slice bread.
Serve as a canape on rye or pumpernickel party bread.
Can be made one day in advance.
Makes 2 pounds or 12 salad portions.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown the hamburger and drain off the fat; set aside.
Mix the other ingredients and simmer 1/2 hour.
Combine with browned beef and simmer another 1/2 hour.

title: raisin and nut shortbread balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Mix well.
Stir in flour.
Mix in raisins and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Place
on
cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Let stand for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: mince oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs and water.
Stir in mincemeat.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately remove from baking sheets.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine 2 sticks butter, confectioners sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat for 10 minutes on medium speed.
Spread over crust.
Dip bananas in lemon juice.
Line over fluffy mixture.
Top with crushed pineapple and maraschino cherries. Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: glazed fruited chicken
directions: Drain fruit salad and set aside.
Reserve 2/3 cup of juice. Stir juice and mayonnaise over medium heat until boiling; add stuffing and spread into 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Add cut up chicken; sprinkle with salt and pepper and brush with mayonnaise.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dang good pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in deep crust pie shell at 350° until firm.

title: pickled beets
directions: You will need 6 pint jars with lids.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy.
Shape dough into balls.
Roll in sugar, then bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. While still hot and just out of oven, press a candy kiss in the middle of each cookie.

title: fudge candies
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add butter, milk and cinnamon.
Stir well and put in refrigerator 1 hour until hardened.
Scoop out small amount the size of a walnut and roll in palm of hands to form balls.
Roll in colored sprinkles, some in coconut or chopped nuts.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add water, wine, vegetables, seasonings and fish fillets.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup milk to flour to make a thin paste.
Add to hot mixture, stirring and cooking until thick.
Gradually add rest of milk, half and half, crab meat and parsley.
Heat thoroughly before serving.

title: border buttermilk
directions: Put lemonade and tequila in 1-quart blender container.
Fill with crushed ice.
Blend briefly until foamy.
Add food coloring if desired.
Serve.

title: peach parfait pie
directions: If using fresh peaches, let stand about 15 minutes after mixing with sugar.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup and heat to boiling.
Add gelatin and stir to dissolve.
Add cold water.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to package directions in layers or 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Prick with fork.
Pour evaporated milk, powdered sugar and vanilla mixture over cake.
Let stand until cool.
Frost with whipped topping and frozen coconut.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt oleo and dip chicken pieces in melted oleo.
Roll in breaded crumb mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour, covered with foil. Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: oriental meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Brown meatballs thoroughly.
Remove meat balls; drain oil.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Add bouillon, green pepper and pineapple.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to skillet.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Add meatballs.
Cover; simmer 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: strawberry slushy
directions: Blend frozen strawberries with ginger ale in blender until slushy.
Garnish each serving each mint.
Serve immediately.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Spread bite-sized bits of lettuce on bottom of large salad bowl.
Sprinkle onion, celery and green pepper in layers on top of lettuce.
Add parboiled peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar on top. Spread 1 pint of mayonnaise on top (like icing) until entirely covered.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese (grated) on top.
Cover with plastic wrap and set in refrigerator for 6 to 8 hours.
Will keep well for 2 to 3 days.

title: sicilian quiche(sausage rolls)
directions: Let dough rise.
Roll out into rectangle.
Spread sausage evenly over dough, also, cheese, parsley, garlic salt and pepper. Roll dough jellyroll fashion.
Place seam side down on cutting board.
Cut into 1-inch slices.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 35 minutes on greased cookie sheet until brown and sausage is done.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease one 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pecans and coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix by directions and pour into pan. Melt together cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar and pour on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until good and brown.

title: peanut butter-chocolate fudge
directions: Combine:
1 1/2 cups sugar, 1/3 cup milk, 6 tablespoons margarine.
Heat in saucepan and bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 4 minutes over medium heat while stirring. Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add 1/2 jar Marshmallow Creme and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir well until blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Repeat this process with remaining ingredients, substituting peanut butter for chocolate chips.
Pour and spread on top of chocolate layer.
Cool and cut into pieces, can be frozen.

title: lay-a-bed stew
directions: Mix and bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Sift dry ingredients, then add milk, egg, vanilla and oil. Beat for 2 minutes; pour into pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes (or until top is light brown).

title: chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Mix chicken, zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate. Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high speed, 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture. Bake about 35 minutes at 400° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Garnish with tomato and zucchini slices, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Slice eggplant in half and scoop out meat.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Add meat of eggplant plus all other ingredients.
Add flour to thicken to proper consistency.
Cook over moderate heat for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Stuff eggplant mixture back into shells.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix and butter with 1 egg.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
With mixer, beat 8 ounces cream cheese, 2 eggs and box of powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pain perdu (lost bread) or french toast
directions: Beat eggs.
Add evaporated milk and sugar and beat well. Grease iron skillet with butter.

Dip bread slices in egg mixture and fry on greased skillet until each side is golden brown. Sprinkle with a little powdered sugar and serve with cold milk. May also be served with cane or maple syrup.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Place pork chops in a lightly greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over pork chops. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together butter, oil and sugar.
Add eggs to this.
Mix together flour, cinnamon and other spices.
Coat raisins, dates and nuts with flour.
Liquify bananas in blender.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: graham cracker jello cake
directions: Place 1/2 of the graham crackers on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cream butter, sugar and egg yolk.
Blend the pineapple and nuts into beaten egg white.
Combine the 2 mixtures and spread on top of graham crackers.
Top with remaining graham crackers.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut stew meat into small pieces.
Brown stew beef in large pot; add 1/4 cup flour and mix.
Add water to cover stew beef.
Add celery and onions; cook on low heat about 1/2 hour.
Add bean sprouts, keep on low heat and cook until bean sprouts are done, about 1 hour.
Add soy sauce; mix well and enjoy.

title: conch fritter
directions: Clean and pound conchs.
Slice very thin or dice very small. In bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine egg with milk and gradually add to center of flour mixture.
Blend gently to make a smooth batter.
Mix conch in batter; fry in deep fat.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Blend in sour cream, oil and creamed corn.
Mix in corn meal.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: pecan fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla, including nuts.
Bring to boil to 240° (very important).
Cook 25 minutes.
Add vanilla. Beat until very thick.
Cut while warm.

title: sour cream swiss steak
directions: Four and season meat brown in frying pan. put meat into a casserole- top with onion slices and mushrooms.
Make gravy in fry pan.
Add cheese and sour cream.

title: amazing coconut pie(quick and easy)
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in an electric blender. Cover and blend on low speed for three minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie dish.
Let stand about five minutes then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all and let set all day.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble (save drippings in the pan).
Add vegetables to the drippings.
Cover the vegetables and cook over a low heat until just tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Add the salt and pepper in the last 2 minutes.
Place in a serving dish and sprinkle the crumbled bacon over the top.
Serves six.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: In a bowl, mix sugar and flour in half and half.
Put dots of butter in bottom of pie shell.
Fill shell completely with filling.
Filling will shrink while baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Melt together marshmallows and chocolate.
Add boiling water and mix until smooth.
Cool.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add vanilla, chocolate mixture and sour cream.
Then add flour, soda and salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Put 1/3 cup of mixture in cup and add hot water.

title: family favorite
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Put into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade b~b~q sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pan and cook for 5 minutes. Then pour into container and refrigerate.
Use as barbecue sauce or steak sauce.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add with milk.
Blend in blueberries.
Spread in a 9 x 11-inch pan and sprinkle with topping made of remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine and combine all ingredients in a buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: *Use vinegar with 5% acidity.

title: rum swizzle
directions: Into 12 ounce Tom Collins glass, put juice of 1 lime/lemon, powdered sugar and carbonated water (lemon/lime soda is okay). Fill glass with shaved ice and stir thoroughly with swizzle stick. Then add bitters and rum.
Fill with soda and serve with swizzle stick in glass.
Individual is to do final stirring.

title: sausage ring
directions: Brown sausage/ham pieces, onion, seasonings and parsley. Drain well and cool.
Beat 1 egg and add to sausage mixture, along with shredded cheese.
Roll out each loaf of bread (use very smooth surface), making a 6 x 18-inch rectangle.
Spoon sausage mixture onto center of dough.
Starting at long ends, roll up dough.
Pinch to seal.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Dredge meat with flour; sear in hot fat in large heavy skillet.
Add paprika; stir so meat is colored.
Remove meat.
Add onions, cook over moderate heat until soft.
Add tomato paste; replace meat.
Add beef broth.
Cook or bake, covered, until meat is done (15 minutes if tenderloin is used; 2 hours for less tender meat, such as round steak).
Season to taste.
Mix cornstarch in cold water.
Add to meat mixture.
Simmer until sauce is smooth and thickened.
Turn off heat.
Add some of the hot sauce to sour cream, then stir sour cream into remaining sauce.
Serve with wide noodles.

title: curried rice salad
directions: In large bowl, combine rice with peppers and onions.
In measuring cup, blend salad oil, vinegar, sugar, lemon juice, curry and salt.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and oil in saucepan; mix well.
Place over medium heat until heated.
Cool.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut in cold water; squeeze dry.
Combine with vegetables; mix well. Pour dressing over it and refrigerate.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together and chill for several hours.

title: railroad pie
directions: Cook beef and onion in skillet until browned.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: verna stiely's caramel icing
directions: Mix and cook to soft ball stage.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat until spreadable.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix well.
Chill 2 hours. Roll into balls, press with fork and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Fold all ingredients together.
Place in well-greased casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving. Makes 4 ample servings or 12 small ones.
Good reheated in microwave.

title: pasta florentine
directions: In food processor or blender, chop garlic.
Add remaining ingredients (except pasta).
Process until well blended.
Spoon over pasta; toss to coat.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 10 cups.

title: hush puppies
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder and salt.
In a small bowl, mix egg and milk.
Stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Drop by tablespoons into hot oil in fryer.
Fry about 2 minutes each side until golden brown. Drain. Serve hot.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add cake mix and flour.
Knead dough.
Let rise until double. Roll out and sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Frost with favorite icing.
(I use 1 cup powdered sugar and enough water to make a thin glaze.)

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Divide mixture and pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie plates.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add zucchini, salt and pepper, green chilies and corn.
Cover and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: chex party mix(microwave recipe)
directions: In a 4-quart bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish, melt butter on High for 1 minute.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Gradually add cereal and nuts, mixing until all pieces are coated.
Microwave on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.

title: tastes great grilled chicken
directions: Use Italian dressing to marinate chicken in overnight.
Cook on grill or bake.
Tastes great.

title: creamy chocolate shake
directions: Place milk, one scoop ice cream and chocolate sauce in blender.
Blend for 2 seconds.
Pour into a glass and top with the other scoop of ice cream.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut chicken into pieces about 1 x 2-inches. Mix soy sauce, maple syrup, sherry, ginger and Chinese five-spice together. Add chicken and marinate 20 minutes, turning once.

title: gertrude white's fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into slices about 1/2 inch thick.
Beat egg and water slightly.
Dip slices in egg and roll in bread crumbs which have been seasoned with salt and pepper.
Allow tomatoes to dry somewhat before frying or place in refrigerator for about 1/2 hour.
Place tomatoes in hot oil in heavy skillet.
Brown on one side and turn carefully.
Reduce heat so tomatoes will have sufficient time to cook before browning.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve at once.

title: broccoli cauliflower toss
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a bowl. Marinate overnight before serving.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chili con carne americano
directions: Use a 12-inch or larger skillet. In a large skillet over medium heat, cook onion, bell pepper, crumbled ground beef, sausage and garlic until meat is lightly brown. Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, chili powder, cayenne, salt and beans; stir to blend. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes, covered. Serves 8 to 10.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Crush crackers until like meal, then in a greased casserole dish, put a layer of drained broccoli, then a layer of cheese and next, a layer of crumbs.
Pour melted oleo over all.
Bake for 20 minutes at 320°.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Make a 1/2-inch layer of slightly crushed crackers in the bottom of one 9-inch pie pan.
Use approximately 8 whole crackers to make side crust by standing them up around the edge of pie pan.

title: glynda raef's blue ribbon caramel fudge cake
directions: Unwrap the caramels the night before starting.
Mix together the butter and sugar. Add eggs, then rest of ingredients.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: candied apple cake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add brown sugar, heat, stirring constantly, until mixture becomes thick and syrupy.
Remove from heat and divide into two 8-inch layer cake pans.
Core and slice apples.
Arrange attractively in syrup and set aside.

title: legendary colorado crab rounds
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, scallions, cheese, Tabasco, curry powder and crab.
To serve, place mixture on bread rounds and broil until golden.
Serve immediately.

title: turkey zucchini parmigiana(a light version of a traditional italian favorite)
directions: *Preferably any of the many whole grains, as golden wheat, oat-wheat, whole wheat, etc.

title: rustic lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions, but do not add salt.
While noodles are cooking, preheat oven to 350°. Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.

title: southern corn bread
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Have a greased (oiled) skillet in a 450° oven.
Pour mixture into medium size skillet.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until browned.

title: snack crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir in crackers.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the cheese, onion, celery and mayo together with the vegetables.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour melted margarine on top along with the crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: garlic potato with crunchy onions
directions: Lightly grease shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole pan. In medium saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, salt and garlic; stir.
Add instant potatoes and sour cream; mix well.
Spoon potatoes into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with onions and cheese.
Bake until brown, maybe 30 to 60 seconds. Makes 8 servings (at 1/2 cup).

title: scalloped potatoes and mushrooms
directions: Peel and slice potatoes thin; place one layer in greased casserole.
Sprinkle with onion, green pepper, salt and pepper. Add more potatoes and another layer of onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Continue until all ingredients are used.
Add 4 cups of milk to cream of mushroom soup and spread over top.
Cover and bake until potatoes are tender at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies in blender a few at a time.
Put half of mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix 1/2 cup butter with the cookie crumbs and spread evenly to form crust.
In separate bowl, mix the 2 boxes of instant pudding with milk.
Mix in Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of crust.
Add remaining cookie crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Beat cream cheese, lemon juice, milk, green onions, liquid smoke and dill weed with a mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in salmon.
Chill overnight for flavors to blend.
Serve on bread or crackers.

title: fried corn on the cob
directions: Heat the oil in a deep fryer to 375 degrees.
Combine the buttermilk and Tabasco in a shallow bowl.
Place corn into buttermilk mixture and turn to coat.
Combine the corn meal, flour, and Essence seasoning. Mix well.
Remove each ear of corn from the buttermilk and place in the cornmeal mixture coating well.
Place on a rack to allow the coating to set.
If needed, coat again with the cornmeal mixture. Carefully drop each ear of corn into the hot oil and fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper. Serve warm.

title: peg bracken's scotch casserole
directions: Cook the macaroni in two quarts of salted water until tender. Blend milk with soup and add beef, cheese, garlic salt and onion. Grease
a large casserole and fill with alternating layers of beef mixture and macaroni.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and dot with butter. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raspberry mint cooler
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 3 cups water, mint and sugar to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes. Stir in raspberries, lemonade concentrate and remaining water. Refrigerate overnight. Strain raspberry mixture, reserving liquid. Press berries and mint through a sieve; discard seeds and mint. Combine raspberry juice with the reserved liquid. Serve over rice.

title: rice hamburger goulash
directions: Cut the green pepper and onion fine.
Saute in a little margarine.
Add hamburger and let simmer slowly until hamburger is done.
After the rice is cooked until about done, drain it.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Put in a large bowl for 24 hours, stirring many times.
Keep in covered tin.

title: clipper chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Using electric mixer, beat first 6 ingredients in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt in small bowl.
Stir into butter mixture.
Mix in chocolate chips and all chopped nuts. Drop batter by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookies sheets, spacing apart.
Bake until cookies are golden brown, about 16 minutes. Transfer cookies to racks and cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: hot milk coffee cake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan with milk.
In bowl, beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to eggs mixture.
Add milk and vanilla.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together. Press in bottom
of pan. Bake 15 minutes at 400°. Next day or when it's cold, mix the filling.

title: lo-fat chicken salsa and fajitas(very quick and easy)
directions: Saute chicken strips in salsa until white.
Add salsa to keep from sticking while cooking.

title: 10 minute french bread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients. Stir together flour and salt. Pour yeast mixture over flour mixture. Knead well or use mixer with dough hook. Place in bowl sprayed with oil spray. Cover with Saran or Saran quick cover and let rise 10 minutes. Punch down. Rise 10 minutes. Punch down. Rise 10 minutes. Punch down (3 times). Then cut dough into 3 sections. Roll into rectangle and shape into loaf. Place on greased/oil/parchment paper cookie sheet and let rise 20 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: tangy glazed ham
directions: Score ham; stud with whole cloves.
Heat ham according to label directions.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice. Combine the reserved juice with remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, to boiling.
Boil 1 minute. During last 30 minutes of baking, brush ham with pineapple glaze several times.
Garnish ham and serving platter with pineapple. Serve extra glaze as sauce over sliced ham.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Spread into crust.
In another bowl, beat milk and pudding mixes on low speed until combined.
Beat on high for 2 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; mix well.
Spread over cheese layer.
Chill.
Garnish with nuts and/or Cool Whip, if desired.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay crescent roll dough out flat (do not separate individual rolls) on a shallow baking pan.
Bake the dough per the directions on the can.
Let cool.
Combine sour cream, cream cheese and dressing to make a sauce.
Cover the crust with sauce.
Top with slices of your favorite vegetables.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sheepherder's breakfast
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp. Drain all but 1/2 cup of the drippings.
Add hash browns to skillet; mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning when browned.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken and cut into chunks. Mix together cheese and Ro-Tel and microwave until it is a consistency to pour. Cook noodles and drain. Mix together chopped chicken, Ro-Tel-cheese mixture, cream of chicken soup and cooked noodles. Mix well and put in a casserole dish. Bake until bubbly.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together except cake mix, nuts and butter. Spread pumpkin mixture in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over pumpkin.
Drizzle melted butter over dry cake mix; bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: dip and chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Crush potato chips.
Dip chicken thighs in egg mixture, then in crushed potato chips.
Place in pan; bake for 20 minutes.
Turn and bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: nut cake
directions: You can mix nuts and raisins, nuts and coconut or use nuts alone or raisins alone.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, 2 at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour, a little at a time, and mix well.
Add vanilla, nuts and apple.

title: craft . . . pine cone birdfeeders
directions: Tie yarn to the top of pine cone.
Cover pine cone with peanut butter, then roll in bird seed.
Hang feeder in tree and watch the birds enjoy.

title: congo squares
directions: Add the eggs; stir with sugar mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash with salt and pepper until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and cook 10 minutes longer.

title: quick beef and noodles
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in all ingredients and 1/2 of cheese.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: giustino's pepperoni bread
directions: In a bowl, mix yeast and water and allow the yeast time to bloom (approximately 10 minutes). In a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour and the blended yeast. Cover well and keep warm. Allow to rise for 1 1/2 hours. Dice pepperoni (1/2 x 1/2 x 1/4) and shred the Swiss cheese. Reserve in bowl.

title: classic meat loaf
directions: Reserve 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
Combine ground beef, remaining tomato sauce, bread crumbs, egg, onion, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt and pepper, mixing thoroughly.
Shape beef mixture into an 8 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Place on rack in an open roasting pan. Combine brown sugar and mustard and blend with reserved tomato sauce.
Spread over top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet.
While this is browning, cook macaroni.
After ground beef is browned, drain excess fat.
Drain water from macaroni.
Mix macaroni, ground beef and cream of mushroom soup together.
Salt and pepper to taste; cook until all ingredients are hot.
Before serving, add sour cream.

title: pudding surprise
directions: Mix together oleo and flour. Put in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: frozen margaritas
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: texas chili
directions: Wash beans, cover with cold water and let stand overnight. Drain beans and place in large saucepan with 2 quarts water.
Bring to boil, then simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and reserve 1 cup liquid. Cut up bacon slices.
Saute in Dutch oven 2 minutes.
Add meat which has been browned and drained of all fat but 1 tablespoon.

title: macaroni with asparagus ham rolls
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk, stirring constantly. When thick, add cheese.
Spread each ham slice with mustard.
Wrap around 3 to 4 asparagus spears.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook
macaroni	in salted water; drain.
Mix
in
tuna. Then add soup and layer top with cheese.
Bake
at
350° until cheese has melted.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tea cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and vanilla until blended well.
Add flour with mixer.
Fold in nuts with spoon.
Roll in a ball the size of marbles.
Take thumb.
Make print in top.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: kraut, potatoes and pork ribs
directions: Cook in pressure cooker on 15 pounds pressure for 18 minutes after cooker starts jiggling.

title: pineapple upside cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat together the first 3 ingredients until sugar and butter are well melted.
Pour remaining ingredients over pineapple mixture in skillet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cake is cooled, invert on cake plate.

title: mini-pizzas
directions: Brown meat (if needed), drain grease.
Flatten biscuits out on a baking sheet (greased or sprayed with Pam).
Spoon a small amount of tomato sauce into each biscuit.
Add a small amount of meat and then a small amount of cheese.
Put in a preheated 450° oven and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 10 mini-pizzas.
Great for children! Great for babysitters, too!

title: new orleans spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Combine with both soups, tomatoes and cheese.
Melt together at medium-low heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil noodles and drain.
Combine with mixture.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Combine and heat until thoroughly melted.
May be microwaved. Stir well until mixed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet baked beans
directions: Place all the ingredients in a large, heavy pot. Cook on low heat for 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: spinach souffle
directions: Combine flour and cheese.
Toss well.
Stir together eggs and milk.
Combine all with spinach, pour into sprayed 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with bacon . Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Pour peeled and sliced apples into unbaked pie crust.
Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and water.
Stir until smooth.
Pour over apples.
Cover with top crust.
Seal edges.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat eggs into sugar, one at a time, until fluffy.
Mix apples and nuts into the dry ingredients and then stir in remaining ingredients.

title: rotel cheese dip
directions: Melt together in saucepan on low heat until smooth.

title: spanish rice
directions: This recipe takes 1 hour
to
prepare
and makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, sour cream, eggs and vanilla. Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Pour half of mixture into pan and sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.
Bake at 375° about 55 minutes.

title: cheddar vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento, and 1/2 of the French fried onions.
Pour into a 1 quart casserole.
Bake covered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake uncovered for 5 minutes longer.

title: oven pepper roast
directions: Rub roast with olive oil; sprinkle lightly with Season-All, garlic and cayenne powder on all sides.
Sprinkle heavily with coarsely ground black pepper on all sides.
Place uncovered in Dutch oven.
Cook at 500° for 7 minutes per pound.
Turn off oven and do not open door for 45 minutes to 1 hour, depending on size of roast.

title: congealed tomato salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add vinegar and tomatoes.
Let set slightly.
Stir; chill until firm.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in hot water and cool.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Mix in 4 egg yolks, one at a time, beating well. Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Combine flour and soda and add alternately with buttermilk to chocolate mixture.
Do not overcream.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans.

title: chocolate butter sweets
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Cream well. Gradually add flour.
Shape by teaspoonfuls into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press hole in center of each.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, until delicably browned.
Fill while warm. Cool frost.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together in Pyrex dish and bake at 375° for 1 hour or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: peachy bread pudding
directions: You will need a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars together.
Add eggs, water and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add flour, salt and soda; beat until smooth. Add chocolate chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto floured cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in bowl; beat until stiff peaks form.
Put in larger bowl and beat on low speed, gradually adding sugar.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; refrigerate until firm.
Spread topping on top (made from sour cream, cream cheese and sugar).

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow the cream cheese to soften. Blend cream cheese and packages of Ranch dressing together and in the Cheddar cheese. Separate mixture into 2 balls. Roll in chopped walnuts. Wrap in plastic wrap and allow to set overnight. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, spice, salt and baking powder.
In second bowl, cream margarine, eggs and pumpkin.
Stir in cranberry sauce and pecans.
Add pumpkin mixture to flour mixture and mix until well moistened.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes, then remove to cooling rack.
Completely cool, then drizzle with glaze.

title: sally's super spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, eggs, green onions and bacon together.
Mix salad oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, garlic powder and lemon juice. Toss over salad mixture.

title: italian nachos
directions: Place thinly sliced sausage on tortilla chips; spread on baking pan.
Top with cheese and broil in oven until cheese melts. If desired, garnish with sour cream.

title: virginia's easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef in a 3-quart saucepan; drain off excess fat.
Add sauce and water; simmer 10 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients except lasagne noodles for filling.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Layer 3 pieces of uncooked lasagne over sauce; cover with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Spread 1/2 of cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake 10 minutes longer. Allow to stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 to 10 servings. Serve with salad and bread.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: If possible, have butcher grind meats together twice to make fine.
Otherwise, mix meats until well-blended.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls.
Fry in butter or oil over medium heat, turning frequently.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered. Cook 20 to 30 minutes total.
Add water if necessary.
For more flavor, fry a sliced onion with the meatballs.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour and mix well. Add water; place over medium heat until mixture begins to thicken. Lower heat and add beaten egg yolks. When blended well, add grated lemon and juice of the lemon. Continue cooking until mixture thickens to the consistency of chocolate pudding. Place in pie shell and top with Cool Whip.

title: cheddar charmer
directions: With butter, lightly grease a low casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the eggs and the milk; beat again.
Toss together cubed bread and Cheddar; place in casserole.
Cover with eggs and milk.
Place a few dabs of butter on top.
Bake for about 45 minutes.
Great with ham!

title: king size cranberry orange muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease king size muffin pan.
Mix cranberries, 1/4 cup sugar and orange peel; set aside.
In large bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except nuts.
In a separate bowl, mix oil, juice and eggs.
Pour all at once into dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.
Add cranberries and nuts.
Divide batter evenly into the muffin cups.
Bake 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes before removing.
Yield: 6 king size muffins.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° until set (about 40 minutes).

title: spiced apple muffinettes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins.
Peel apple and slice in half.
Remove center core and cut apple into small slices (dice).
Beat butter and sugar in bowl until mixture is creamy and pale yellow.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Mix flour, a spoonful at a time, then baking powder and cinnamon.
Add apple chunks and applesauce and stir with a rubber spatula.
Spoon evenly into muffin tins.
For 24 miniature muffins, bake 20 minutes.
For 12 regular size muffins, bake 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and enjoy.

title: garlic-parsley potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper in a large bowl; toss to coat well.
Place half of mixture in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Sprinkle half of parsley over potatoes.
Add remaining potato mixture.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes, or until tender.
Uncover; sprinkle remaining parsley over potatoes.

title: smothered burritos
directions: Brown ground round.
Add chili powder to taste.
Heat the refried beans, the cream of chicken soup (with the chiles and diced chicken stirred in) in separate pans.
Take one flour tortilla and spread beans on bottom; follow up with ground round. Roll together and then top with soup, chicken, chile mixture.
Add any remaining toppings you like such as lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and onions and eat.

title: stollen bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Cut all fruit and nuts together as small as you want.
Scald milk in double boiler over low heat.
Add sugar and salt; mix.
Cool and add yeast and 3 cups flour; beat well.
Add remaining flour and mix until dough forms a ball free from bowl.
Knead on floured board; place in greased bowl.
Let rise to double in size.
Punch down.
Roll out to 9 x 12 inch rectangle.
Cover with fruit, nuts and roll up like jelly roll.
Brush top with oil.
Let rise until double in size.
Bake at 375°.
Cover with powdered sugar or make your own white icing.
Add a few fruits and nuts on top.
So good!

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes.
Place in microwave dish with lid. Quarter onion and separate and place on top of potatoes.
Cut butter over potatoes and microwave on High power approximately 20 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Cooking time will depend on microwave wattage and amount of potatoes.

title: artichoke quiche
directions: Chop artichoke hearts.
Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an ungreased glass dish (13 x 9-inch) for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: beef roulades
directions: Place onion, cubed, on meat.
Put 1 1/2 slices of bacon on onion and a couple of shakes of garlic powder.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Place in pot with
consomme and cook on medium heat about 45 minutes.
Thicken.
Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: chili rice verde
directions: Put rice vermicelli in boiling water and cook for 2 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Flush rice vermicelli with cold water or tap water for 2 minutes, then it can be finally treated rice vermicelli in soup and other different ways, e.g. fried rice vermicelli, cold-dressed rice vermicelli, etc.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, bananas, salt, sour cream and vanilla.
Mix together flour and baking soda.
Add to butter mixture.
Add nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coke chicken
directions: Cut up chicken.
Place in iron skillet.
Mix 1/2 Coke and 1/2 cup catsup.
Smooth over chicken and cook it for 15 minutes.
Mix remaining Coke and catsup.
Turn over the chicken and place remaining mix over chicken.
Cook 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: idaho chili(vegetarian)
directions: In a 4 1/2 quart Dutch oven, stir together all ingredients, except sour cream and chips.
Bring mixture to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, at least 30 minutes.
Spoon into bowls. Top each serving with sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 6 to 8 main dish servings.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, powered sugar and margarine.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze for approximately 30 minutes.
Melt chocolate.
Stick tooth picks into balls and dip in chocolate.
Leave a little on top to make it look like a buckeye. Place on cookie sheet lined with wax paper to cool.

title: lena's salmon croquettes
directions: Put all ingredients (including the liquid from salmon) into a mixing bowl.
Break salmon so there are no lumps.
Stir briskly so all ingredients are well mixed.
Do not let mixture set.
Use right away.
Heat enough oil in fryer so that croquettes can float to the top.
Scoop a rounded tablespoonful of mixture and slide into hot oil.
Croquettes brown quickly.
Turn a couple of times. After fried evenly, remove with a slotted spoon and place on a paper towel to absorb oil.
Serve hot!

title: party chicken salad
directions: Cook the chicken in salted water.
Cool and dice.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and salt.
Chill for several hours.
Add celery, grapes, chopped eggs, mayonnaise and almonds.
Toss lightly.
Season salad with salt to taste.
Serve on lettuce leaf or in lettuce lined bowl.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: tasty 4 gram of fat lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water 10 minutes.
While noodles cook, in a medium pan put sauce, onion (chopped), oregano, garlics, spaghetti mix and tomatoes (chopped) and beat just until powders are dissolved.
Spray large oven dish with nonfat spray.
Place a thin layer of sauce mixture over the bottom of dish.
Place one layer of noodles longways across the dish.
Put sauce on noodles and then a layer of cottage cheese (3/4 cup), then sauce, noodles and cottage cheese.
Place noodles on the top with nonfat cheese. Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes and then enjoy!!!

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Mix soups and cheese. Pour over vegetables in casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Add onion rings.
Cook 10 minutes more.

title: kielbasa dip
directions: Grate beets and let drain, then mix with horseradish.
Mix sugar and vinegar together.
When sugar has dissolved, mix with beets and horseradish and add salt and pepper to taste.
Set kielbasa slices on platter and use beets with horseradish as dip. Can also be used as condiment for ham.

title: homemade baking powder
directions: Sift all ingredients together and store in a tight container.

title: christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Add peanut butter, then add chow mein noodles.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and let stand an hour until cool.
Makes a delicious candy for Christmas.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add vegetables and saute until tender.
Add soup, seasonings and bouillon cubes dissolved in the hot water. Cover with foil.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: susie's chicken
directions: In large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onion and chicken.
Cook on medium-high until chicken turns white (5 to 8 minutes).
Add tomatoes, beans, peppers and spices.
Cook, covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour over rice and top with 1 tablespoon sour cream.
Serve with salad and/or bread.
A real family favorite!
Enjoy!

title: double-quick dinner rolls
directions: In bowl dissolve yeast in water.
Measure flour by dip-level-pour method or by sifting.
Stir sugar, half of flour and salt into yeast.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Add egg and shortening.
Beat in rest of flour until smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl and cover with cloth.
Let rise in warm place (85°) until double, about 30 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Beat eggs, flour, pepper and oregano.
Gradually stir in milk. Grease oblong Pyrex dish.
Place 1/2 cheese and cut 1/2 of pepperoni in small slices on bottom of dish.
Add the rest of the cheese and pepperoni to egg mixture and stir.
Pour into dish. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.

title: beef salami
directions: Mix all ingredients together with hands and shape into 2 rolls. Wrap tightly with foil and refrigerate for 2 days.
Now place in shallow pan. Prick holes in top of foil rolls to let steam escape.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Eat either hot or cold. May be frozen.

title: clam-corn casserole
directions: Drain liquid from clams.
Add milk to make 1 cup.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) until firm, about 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all veggies.
Combine other ingredients and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: energy bars
directions: Grease a piece of aluminum foil to fit a cookie sheet.
Bake the oats on a cookie sheet at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk crumb cake
directions: Add and mix until well blended.
Pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Spoon undiluted soup over all.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours on low or 4 hours on high.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 2-quart casserole dish combine beans, soup and 1/2 can onions.
Heat milk and Cheez Whiz until cheese is melted.
Stir into bean mixture.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Dip pecans in egg whites, then roll in sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
When oven reaches 500°, turn it off and place pecans in oven.
Stir often until oven is cool.

title: victorian cookies
directions: Cream together cream cheese and butter until smooth and light. Beat in lemon rind.
Mix in separate bowl, flour and sugar.
Stir in half of flour mixture to creamed mixture, blending well.
Stir in remaining flour.
Roll dough out onto a lightly floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 2-inch rounds.
Spoon 1/2 teaspoon of preserves in center of each round.
Form a triangle by folding in 3 edges.
Pinch edges gently.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool cookies and store in airtight tin.

title: irish potatoes
directions: Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add vanilla to mix.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Add coconut.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Roll in cinnamon after forming small balls.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix together and let set.

title: catherine's holiday fruit salad
directions: Chop apples and bananas.
Slice and seed grapes or use seedless.
Stir in pecans and mix well.
Add Marshmallow Creme and mayonnaise to desired consistency.
Chill for at least one hour.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions.
Add potatoes, salt and pepper.
Stir constantly with broth for 10 minutes or until starting to thicken. Add milk and stir with broccoli.

title: chicken and egg pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 12 baking dish. Boil chicken nuggets in broth until done. Remove chicken and strain broth. Reserve 3 cups. In 4-quart saucepan, melt butter. Add flour, stirring until bubbling and foamy. Do not brown. Whisk in reserved broth. Add salt and pepper, stirring until smooth and thick. Remove from heat. Add mushrooms, peas and carrots and chopped eggs. Pour into casserole. Roll pastry to 14 x 11-inch rectangle. Place on top of casserole. Fold under excess pastry. Do not stretch pastry. Crimp edges with fork. Cut 6 (1-inch) slits in top of pastry. Brush top of pastry with egg mixture. Bake 35 minutes or until golden.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Add remaining milk, pineapple and pudding.
Beat 1 minute.
Pour into bowl and chill.

title: the best wild rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours or until liquid is gone.
Serves 8.
Foolproof recipe and absolutely delicious.

title: strawberry ice cream pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the hot water; chill in fridge until practically set.
Beat in ice cream with beater.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into prebaked pie crust.
Chill until set.

title: dirt cake
directions: Chop Oreo cookies in blender until it looks like dirt.
It helps to do a few cookies at a time.
Put into a large bowl; set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together the butter, cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Set this aside.
In a super large bowl, mix together the pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Mix until it gets a little thick.
Mix the cream cheese and pudding mixtures together. Layer dirt mix first, then filling.
Continue to layer until dirt is on the top layer.
Let sit overnight, but not necessary.

title: casserole for the crowd
directions: Cook hamburger meat until done.
"Do not drain."
Add onion and cook until tender.
Mix rest of ingredients (except bread crumbs) together.
Put in large casserole bowl.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until hot all the way through.
It can be made a day ahead and just reheated when you want to serve it.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix in order given. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: 1-2-3 brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Spread in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool; frost.

title: swamp cabbage and sausage
directions: Clean swamp cabbage and break into small pieces (only tender part of cabbage).
Fry white bacon and reserve a little of the fat.
Fry sausage and cut into small pieces.
Put bacon and small amount of fat into pot.
Add cabbage.
Cover with water. Boil for few minutes.
Add sausage, sugar, salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken salad
directions: Place chopped vegetables in bowl and cover with salad dressing to marinate overnight. When ready to serve, drain off any excess dressing from vegetables and add chicken. Gradually add mayonnaise until salad is of desired consistency. Season to taste with salt and paprika. Serve on lettuce leaves or on croissants.

title: summer squash casserole(low-fat)
directions: Place squash, onion and green pepper in a vegetable steamer over boiling water.
Cover and steam 10 to 12 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Cut up all ingredients and cook in Dutch oven on low for 1 to 2
hours or until vegetables are done.
Serve hot.

title: macaroni "n" cheese pizza
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain. In a bowl, beat the eggs; stir in Cheddar cheese and macaroni. Spread onto a 14-inch pizza pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding supreme
directions: Mix first four ingredients until smooth. Layer wafer, bananas and part of pudding mixture, ending with the pudding on top. Crush a few wafers and sprinkle on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Put candies in the water and let them sit for awhile to partially dissolve.
Heat the mixture to boiling.
Add jello and applesauce.
Chill.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour mixture over flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Add to mixture the soda dissolved in buttermilk; add eggs and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: amish fudgesicles
directions: Beat together and freeze.

title: busy day fruit cobbler
directions: Put fruit in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
If fruit is very juicy, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with each cup juice.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg.
Add flour and milk.
Mix until smooth. Pour over fruit in pan.
Bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: hearty corned beef salad
directions: Pour boiling
water
on
gelatin
in
large bowl.
Stir until gelatin
is
dissolved.
Stir
in
vinegar,
refrigerate until slightly thickened,
about 1 hour.	Break up corned beef with fork.
Stir
corned beef and remaining ingredients except salad greens into
gelatin
mixture.
Pour into 6 1/2 cup ring mold. Refrigerate until
set, at least 2 hours.
Salad can be stored in refrigerator up to 48 hours.
Fifteen minutes before serving, unmold on salad greens.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cottage cheese jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add milk, salad dressing, cottage cheese and grated carrot.
(I use a blender and just blend in the order given.)
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Sets quickly.

title: perfect pina colada
directions: Mix and serve over ice.
Makes 1 serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Put the tortilla chips on right before serving.
Pour dressing on mixture.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water; add strawberries, pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Let set until firm and spread with Cool Whip.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Roll in hand to make small balls about 3/4 inch thick.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while hot. Repeat when cool.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: maypo coffee cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a bowl; break in egg.
Add milk and mix well.
Add shortening and place in greased 10 or 12-inch cake pan. Spread with topping made by creaming together 2 tablespoons soft butter, 4 tablespoon sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 2 tablespoons flour.
Dot with chopped nutmeats.
Bake 25 minutes in oven at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: christmas morning breakfast eggs
directions: Put bread cubes in bottom of a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs and milk; beat together and add peppers and onions.
Add salt and pepper and pour over pan contents.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn chowder
directions: Heat water to boiling. Slowly stir in soup mix. Cover and let simmer for 5 minutes. Add corn and milk, stirring constantly. Add pimento. Cook for 5 minutes over low heat, stirring often.

title: chili con queso
directions: Bring to a boil and serve with corn chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven in iron skillet.

title: charlie bread
directions: Mix together and pour into a Pyrex dish.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix. Cook pudding.
Cool.
Add peanut butter and sugar.
Pour into a baked pie shell.
Use Cool Whip or real whipped cream for topping.

title: doreen's chicken breasts
directions: Melt the margarine and brush the bottom of a 9-inch baking dish with some of the melted margarine.
Put the bread, the parsley and the garlic in a blender or food processor and make crumbs.
Put the crumbs in a small bowl with the rest of the margarine and lemon juice.
Sprinkle the chicken with lite salt and pepper and place in the baking dish.
Add the wine and bake for 5 minutes.
Turn the chicken breasts and bake for another 5 minutes.

title: bacon yum yums
directions: Mix sugar and mustard, line two sheet cake pans with foil.
Lay bacon out, sprinkle with mixture and bake at 250° for 1 hour or more.
Drain on paper towels, cut into bite-size pieces.

title: afterglow cheesecake
directions: Mix to dissolve sugar.
Spread on cooled (10 minutes) cheesecake.
Bake an additional 5 minutes for topping to set. Watch carefully not to scorch or dry out.
Cool to taste.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake according to package directions. Cool. Prepare pudding according to package directions; set aside. Crumble the cake; reserve 1/2 cup. Place half of the remaining cake crumbs in the bottom of a 4 1/2 or 5-quart trifle dish or decorative glass bowl (punch bowl would work). Layer with half of the coffee, half of the pudding, half of the whipped topping and half of the crushed candy bars. Repeat the layers of cake, coffee, pudding and whipped topping. Combine remaining crushed candy bars with reserved cake crumbs. Sprinkle over top. Refrigerate 4 or 5 hours before serving. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: grandma's chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift in flour, cocoa, soda and powder.
Add boiling water and beat until smooth.
Pour into cake dish.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: hot tuna canapes(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients in small mixing bowl.
Use enough mayo just to moisten ingredients.
Spread mixture on Melba toast or crackers.
