Place canapes on plate and microwave on High for 1 minute.
Give dish 1/2 turn twice during cooking.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix well at medium speed until blended.
Pour batter in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. For best result, refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Simmer the onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in butter for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook until the potatoes are tender.
Add tomatoes, clams and their juice, salt, pepper, thyme and cayenne to taste.
Bring chowder to boil.
Add chopped parsley and pour soup into tureen over crackers.

title: different chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Melt margarine and mix with crushed potato chips.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May add grated Cheddar cheese to casserole (1 1/2 to 2 cups).

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Scald milk and add to chocolate mixture.
Mix flour, sugar and salt together. Beat egg yolk and add dry ingredients to eggs.
Add 1 cup hot mixture to egg mixture.
Mix well and add to chocolate mixture in double boiler.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Let cool. Add vanilla and put in baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites and put on pie.
Bake until meringue is browned.

title: butter dip breadsticks
directions: Place butter in an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1 inch baking pan.
In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt; mix well.
Stir in milk just until moistened.
Turn onto a floured surface; knead 10 times.
Roll into a 12 x 9 inch rectangle. Cut into 9 x 1/2 inch strips.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Separate eggs, beat whites, then set aside.
Beat yolks and sugar.
Combine yolk mixture with condensed milk and flavoring, then fold in whites.
Pour into ice cream freezer.
Finish filling freezer to the full line with sweet milk.
Freeze according to freezer directions for a 1 1/2 gallon freezer.

title: veal piccata
directions: Pound veal lightly until very thin. Dredge with flour and season with salt and pepper. Dip in egg, then bread crumbs.
Heat the butter and lemon in a large skillet. Add the veal.

Cook on both sides for 3 to 4 minutes over medium heat with mushrooms. Add the wine, just prior to removing the veal from the skillet. Serve on a hot platter with slices of lemon and parsley. Serves 4.

title: rice pudding
directions: In top of double boiler, combine rice, boiling water and salt. Cook, covered, over medium heat, about 40 minutes or until rice is tender.
Water in bottom of double boiler should be boiling. More boiling water may have to be added.
Do not drain.
Stir in condensed milk and butter.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add raisins and vanilla.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar, egg, fruit cocktail and vanilla and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Saute in enough olive oil to coat bottom of skillet and put 5 or 6 pats of margarine on top of cabbage.
Cook on medium heat until done.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together for 5 minutes in salted water. Drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots.
Fold into drained squash and onion.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti noodles and drain; set aside.
Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and Rotel tomatoes to hamburger.	Simmer.
Spray large baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Mix noodles with sauce mixture and gently stir.
Pour into baking dish.
Add layer of pepperoni to top, then mozzarella cheese, and finally parmesan cheese.
Cover loosely with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until heated through and bubbly. Remove foil and heat 5 minutes more.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix. Store in large bowl, covered, overnight. Then can put in smaller storage containers. Serve as side dish.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix tomato sauce, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Pour 1/2 the tomato mixture in large mixing bowl.
Add egg, salt, pepper and crackers; blend well.
Add beef and onion; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into loaf in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread with remaining tomato mixture.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: crunchy bars
directions: Heat (do not boil) first 3 ingredients. Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan and smooth out. Frost with melted Hershey bars or chocolate icing.

title: louis rauch's fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil for 2 minutes. Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Then add all chocolates and stir until melted.
Pour into greased pan.
Cut into cubes when set.
Refrigerate to store.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all together.
Roll in balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Refrigerate 3 days before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend water, sugar and cornstarch.
Bring to boil until thick and clear (will not be real thick).
Take off stove and add jello mix.
Pour over strawberries in pie shells.
Jell.
Will make 2 pies.

title: quick and easy spinach lasagne
directions: In a large bowl, mix Ricotta, 1 cup Mozzarella, egg, spinach and seasonings.
In greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer:
1/2 cup sauce, 1/3 of uncooked lasagne noodles and 1/2 of spinach. Repeat, then finish with the last 1/3 of the noodles and the remaining sauce.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Mozzarella over the top.
Pour the water around the edges.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stand 15 minutes, then serve.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cook lentils in 4 quarts of water for 1 hour.
Season water and lentils with salt, pepper, garlic powder and 1 bay leaf. Saute in 1/4 pound oleo the onions, carrots, potatoes and celery. Season with salt and pepper.
Add to cooked lentil soup.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add the chopped hot dogs.
Bring to boil 5 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat soup and milk until it starts to boil.
Add salt and pepper, then dots of margarine.
Pour soup over top. Bake until done at 400° for 30 minutes. Top with bread crumbs at the last few minutes, if desired.

title: laura osgood bean's sourdough starter
directions: Pour milk into glass or ceramic bowl.
Cover with cheesecloth. Let stand outdoors for 1 day.
Stir in flour, re-cover and let stand outdoors for 2 days.
Bring indoors to sunny spot; let stand until mixture bubbles and starts to sour.
Spoon into quart jar with screw-top and store in refrigerator 1 day.

title: lemon barbecue meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Precook onion in microwave for 2 minutes.
In a large bowl, mix other ingredients and add onion.
Shape into 6 to 8 little loaves.
Place in a glass baking dish and bake in microwave for 4 minutes on High.

title: artichoke nibbles
directions: Blend cream cheese, chili sauce, parsley, onion and hot pepper sauce; gradually stir in drained tuna.
Beat until mixture is thoroughly blended.
Pack in a 4-cup mold or small bowl; chill thoroughly at least 3 hours.
If desired, garnish with sliced stuffed green olives.
Makes 3 cups pate.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding, butter, egg and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan. Drain peaches, saving 3 tablespoons peach juice.
Place peaches over batter.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tablespoons peach juice.
Beat 2 minutes.
Spoon over peaches within 1-inch of the edge of the batter.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Drain hominy and mix with rest of ingredients.
Bake at 325° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dill beans
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine; add beans. Sprinkle with garlic salt and dill weed.
Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes, stir in 1/2 cup of milk. Spread in butter greased baking dish. In sauce pan add: stick butter, 1/2 c. milk, and 2 c. brown sugar. Heat on stove until sugar is dissolved. pour mixture over potatoes. Cover top with chopped pecans. Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: gourmet crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl and make into cakes. Optional:
Coat the cakes with bread crumbs.

title: good chicken
directions: Mix soup, preserves and dressing.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours or until done at 350°.

title: maple nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend dry ingredients in bowl.
Add milk, egg and flavoring.
Mix until dry ingredients are moist; stir in nuts.
Pour in pan and bake 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° until golden brown.
You may add raisins, if desired.

title: pull apart coffee cake
directions: Place chopped pecans in bottom of Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls on top of pecans.
Mix dry ingredients and sprinkle over frozen rolls.
Pour melted butter over all.
Let rise 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Turn out immediately.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin dip
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream sugar & cream cheese. Beat in remaining ingredients. Store in air tight container in refrigerator. Serve with ginger snaps or apples.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Shake biscuit squares (a few at a time) in the sugar-cinnamon mixture and drop into a greased Bundt pan.
Melt oleo and stir in remaining sugar mixture.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine peanuts, peanut butter, dry milk, powdered sugar and butter.
Beat with a mixer until creamy, about 5 minutes.
Dip the mixture into the candy wrappers.
Beat chocolate to soften (according to directions on can).
Pour a little bit of the chocolate over each piece of candy in each wrapper.

title: bessie's homemade rolls
directions: Mix water, yeast, sugar, butter and salt, then add eggs and potatoes.
Fold in flour.
Let rise.
Place on floured surface; roll out.
Cut out rolls or make cloverleafs.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Let set in refrigerator for several days before serving.

title: praline cookies
directions: Melt butter and stir in sugar.
Mix in beaten eggs, nuts, flour and vanilla thoroughly.
Grease cookie sheet.
Coat with flour.
Drop from teaspoon about 5 inches apart to allow for spreading.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Wait a minute before removing from pan.

title: baked bean and ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add seasoning ingredients and mix well. Salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serve with hot bread and garden salad.

title: sweet sour sauce
directions: Mix together sugar, mustard and molasses.
Add vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Mix well and heat.
Serve hot.

title: haystacks
directions: Melt chips in microwave oven until completely dissolved.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: salsa chip dip
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together until brown.
Add hamburger and onion to other ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine and sugar and add peaches.
Set aside.
Add brandy to peaches.
Pour in baking dish and spoon on topping.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Combine all vegetables in a large bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Pour vinegar mixture over vegetables.
Mix well.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: sour cream pear pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend well.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 minutes, then add topping.

title: four square pudding
directions: Remove crusts from bread, spread slices with butter.
Cut into squares and arrange in layers in an 8-inch greased baking dish. Sprinkle each layer with raisins and bran.
Beat egg yolks.
Add 2 tablespoons of the sugar, nutmeg, milk and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly and pour over bread.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cover with meringue made of stiffly beaten egg whites and remaining sugar.
Bake in slow oven at 300° about 20 minutes or until meringue is lightly browned on top.

title: stroganoff skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender.
(Use shortening if necessary.)
Stir to separate meat.
Drain grease and blot with paper towels.
Gradually blend in remaining ingredients. Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until noodles are done.
Stir often.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper; drain well.
Put into soup pot.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 4 hours. Taste for seasoning.
Serve over rice with shredded cheese and minced green onion.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Serves 8.
Recipe can be doubled, divided into smaller containers and frozen until needed.

title: apple salad
directions: Boil all together and cool.
When ready to use, add apples, bananas, raisins and nuts.

title: salmon loaf with sauce piquant
directions: Combine salmon, crumbs, chopped onion, butter and salt. Combine milk and egg and add to salmon mixture.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf and place on shallow baking pan or in small loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with Sauce Piquant.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. Mix in milk, egg yolks and 1 small can Carnation milk, then add enough regular milk to make 2 cups. Mix well. Add margarine. Microwave on High for 8 minutes. Stir in 4 minutes. Pour into baked pie shell. Whip egg whites and put on top. Bake until brown.

title: spicy hotdogs
directions: Slice hot dogs in bite size pieces.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour barbecue sauce over hot dogs and stir.
Cover and cook on high for 3 or 4 hours.
They are done when they swell up.
Serve with toothpicks or place in warming dish with serving spoon.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping the bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping the bowl occasionally; pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) 60 to 65 minutes, layer cakes 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.
Frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: mother momeyer's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk and egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add milk and egg whites last.
This recipe makes 2 pies.

title: carbonear
directions: Melt butter, add ham and 3 quarters of cream.
Cook over low heat until cream has thickened or cooked down some.
Blend rest of cream with egg yolks.
Add that to hot mixture (mix a little hot cream with cold before pouring it all together).
Stir 1/2 minute over low heat.
Add a little salt and pepper.
Mix in with spaghetti and toss it!

title: dream cicle candy
directions: Cook over medium heat stirring constantly.
When it boils, cook for 7 minutes, continue stirring.
Remove from the stove and add small jar marshmallow cream, 1 bag white chocolate chips, and mix until smooth.
Take out 1 cup and set aside.
Stir the
food coloring into the rest.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9x13 pan.
Pour the cup that you took out over the top and swirl with a knife. Cool and cut into squares.

title: red potato salad
directions: Quarter the potatoes and boil until you can pierce with a fork. Drain potatoes.
In a large bowl, add potatoes, Lipton vegetable soup mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 2 hours before serving.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Place split English muffin halves on a cookie sheet.
Spoon spaghetti sauce onto English muffins.
Place other ingredients onto each English muffin half.
(Put what you like on the muffins.) Cover with shredded cheese.
Place in oven for 10 to 15 minutes with oven at 350°.
Makes 12 mini pizzas.

title: hickory nut pie
directions: Mix together ingredients in order given.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: summer fruit bowl
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, cook water, sugar and lime juice 15 minutes or until mixture becomes a light syrup. Stir in mint leaves; cover and refrigerate until well chilled. Cut watermelon into bite-sized pieces; discard seeds.
Cut unpeeled plums and nectarines into wedges.
Combine cut up fruits with grapes and arrange in very large bowl.
Pour chilled syrup through strainer over fruit; gently toss to mix well.
Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors, stirring mixture occasionally. Serves 20.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Combine cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Set aside. Combine spaghetti sauce and ground beef.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla.
Blend in flour and nuts. Shape into 3/4-inch balls rolling in palm of hands.
Space about 1/2 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 30 minutes.
Cookies should be creamy color.
Remove to wire rack until warm and roll in powdered sugar.
Cool entirely and roll in powdered sugar again if desired.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and rinse artichoke hearts.
Separate and mash with fork.
Mix together with cheese and mayonnaise. Sprinkle with pepper and pinch of garlic powder.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with melba toast rounds

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla.
Spread evenly into wax paper-lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: sharon's frosting
directions: On medium heat in saucepan, mix flour and milk. Keep stirring until thick.
Let flour and milk cool.
Cream together shortening, sugar and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Add mixture that's cooling and beat on high until real creamy.
Add vanilla.
Make sure cake is cool before frosting.

title: salmon bake
directions: Mix together and put in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°
for 50 minutes.

title: johnny marzette
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and put in a baking dish.
Warm in the oven.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in casserole.
Mix first 5 ingredients together. Pour batter into oleo (do not beat).
Stir with fork and then pour fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 days, stirring every day.
Spoon into plastic containers and freeze.
(Use slaw cutter for easier slicing.)

title: banana-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and add oil, egg, bananas, oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon about 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie and 10 to 11 minutes for a crispy cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire cooling rack.
Store in tightly covered container.

title: cornmeal muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine egg, sour cream and shortening.
Add dry ingredients; stir until moistened.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Boil chicken until done and dice.
Dip in Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Cook noodles; rinse and drain.
Heat soup, milk, salt and Italian seasoning.
Stir in cream cheese and cottage cheese while mix is still warm.
Saute mushrooms, onion and bell peppers.
Mix in parsley.
In a 13 x 9-dish, layer the noodles and soup mix.
Layer the
chicken, mushrooms and onion. Repeat until dish is full.
Top with bread crumbs.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: kathy's toffee bars
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour and oatmeal.
Butter jelly roll pan and spread mixture.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Melt chocolate and frost toffee bars.
If desired, may spread chopped walnuts on chocolate.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine chocolate chips and butter in a medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add condensed milk; mix well.
Add flour, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon of dough around each kiss, covering completely.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes. Do not overbake.
Melt white chocolate and shortening.
Drizzle over cookies.
Store in a tightly covered container.

title: health muffins
directions: Mix together
the
flour, bran, baking powder, salt and baking soda and set aside.
Thoroughly blend molasses, yogurt, egg and melted
butter and add to dry ingredients.	Add mashed bananas; add raisins,
if
desired.	Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cabbage-ham soup
directions: In a large soup pot, saute green pepper, celery, onion and parsley in 2 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add ham and cook until heated.
Blend flour and chicken stock or broth in a bowl. Add to ham mixture.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Decrease to low heat and simmer.
Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in a pan.
Add cabbage and water and cook until soft.
Add to broth mixture and cook for another 5 minutes.
Garnish each serving with sour cream.

title: cool-as-a-cucumber salad(in honor of judge nat u. hill)
directions: Mix the lime Jell-O (lemon Jell-O if preferred) and the boiling water; stir until dissolved.
Let cool.
Add cucumber, cottage cheese and onion, mixing well.
Add dressing and mix well again.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish; chill until set.

title: turkey-stuffed peppers for two
directions: Cook peppers in boiling water for 3 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water; set aside.
In a skillet, cook turkey, onion and garlic until meat is no longer pink; drain fat and set aside.
In same skillet, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth.
Gradually add milk; bring to boil, stirring constantly, for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Return turkey to skillet.
Stir in tomato and 2 tablespoons cheese.
Heat through.
Spoon mixture into peppers.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place in greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: cranberry pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to
Grease
a	9
x
5-inch
loaf pan. Cream together butter
and
sugar,
then	beat in the eggs and vanilla. Sift
together
flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices.
Add to	the
egg mixture and blend just until smooth. Mix in pumpkin, berries
and nuts.	Blend briefly.	Pour into pan.	Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: craisin cashew salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces. Wash, core and chop apples (unpeeled) into bite size pieces. Mix and toss all ingredients together in salad bowl with dressing. Serves 10+. Can do ahead.

title: italian bread with tomato appetizers
directions: In small bowl, combine tomatoes, onion, basil, pepper and 2 tablespoons dressing; set aside.
Slice bread diagonally into 8 slices, about 1-inch each.
Brush one side of each slice with remaining dressing.
Broil until golden, turning once.
Top grilled slices with tomato mixture.

title: rich chocolate pie
directions: Mix margarine (warm, not melted) with flour and nuts.
Press into two pie pans or one 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt all ingredients together over low heat. Keep stirring. When mixed well, toss with cooked noodles.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and pat in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; mix soup and Cheez Whiz over medium heat until well blended.
Put vegetables in a 9 x 13-inch and pour the soup mixture over the vegetables.
Top with fried onions.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve
yeast
in
water
(lukewarm).
Sift flour and sugar together.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and water; stir until elastic-like strands form.
Place dough in greased bowl and cover. Let
dough
rise
minutes
or until doubled in bulk.
Shape rolls
and bake on greased pan in preheated 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Mix soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Layer in a 10 x 12-inch lasagna pan the soup, tortillas, chicken, onion and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Bake in a greased pan one hour at 325°.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and water for 2 minutes.
Let it cool. Shred cabbage; salt lightly.
Let stand 1 hour, then squeeze juice from cabbage.
Add celery, green pepper and celery seed.
Moisten with cooled vinegar mixture to cover cabbage.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix soup, milk, rice, mushrooms, carrots, onion powder and onions in an ungreased rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Nestle chicken into rice mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken taco salad
directions: Stir-fry chicken in oil over medium-high heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in salsa; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir together the salad dressing, avocado and hot pepper sauce.

title: fish cakes with mustard sauce(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine the mustard, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Add the vinegar and lemon juice and beat in the oil with a whisk until the mixture is smooth.
Stir in the parsley, dill and chopped gherkins, cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: grit iron casserole
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Brown hamburg and onion in large frying pan.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except spaghetti, in frypan and heat.
Pour over spaghetti in large baking dish.
Mix well.
Top with grated sharp cheese or Mozzarella.
Bake in 350° oven only until cheese is melted.

title: gouda cheese bread
directions: Flatten 1/2 can of crescent rolls on cookie sheet in a neat square.
Place Gouda cheese on crescent square.
Cover with remaining crescent rolls and pinch edges together.	Brush with melted butter and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until lightly brown on top.
Serve immediately.

title: summer cantaloupe salad
directions: Peel and seed cantaloupe and honeydew; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Peel papaya and cut into bite sized pieces.
Combine melons, papaya and grapes in a large bowl.
Chill until serving time.
Combine yogurt, preserves and orange juice in a small bowl. Blend well.
Add to salad; mix well.
Serves 8.

title: scalloped potatoes supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and the 2 cups corn flakes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top it with the 1/2 cup cheese and corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Delicious, quick and easy.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place milk in pan on medium heat with 1 stick margarine.
Let melt.
Mix the warm water and yeast.
Dissolve and set aside.

Mix flour, oatmeal, potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk and yeast. Roll out and top with sugar, cinnamon and nuts. Roll like a jelly roll. Cut in thin slices and place in baking pan. Bake 30 minutes or until done. Drizzle with powdered sugar, water and vanilla.

title: german potato dumpling
directions: Boil potatoes until fork pokes through.
Peel and mash while hot!
Add salt and flour to form patties 1/2-inch thick.
Cook patties in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and place in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan and layer with cheese and onion.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Add butter to carrots while mashing.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and cinnamon; then add to mashed carrots.
Beat eggs and add to mixture last.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: icebox lemonade pie
directions: In bowl, put condensed milk and lemonade; beat until thickened and fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and mix thoroughly.
Put in graham cracker crust and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix to spreading consistency, adding additional milk if necessary.

title: meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and salt.
Cook until thick and clear. Cool.
Beat egg whites until they peak.
Continue beating while adding cooked mixture. Beat 5 minutes.
Pile on pie, sealing edges to crust.
Bake at 450° until golden.

title: chicken adobo
directions: Combine soy sauce and water.
Mix onion, vinegar, soy sauce, water and garlic together and pour over chicken.
Marinate 2 to 4 hours.
Simmer all together 30 to 45 minutes or until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.
Should be marinated in nonmetal dish. May be baked in 350° oven also.

title: bar-b-que chicken (or pork loin)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 15 minutes.
Rub chicken with salt and pepper.
Place chicken in baking dish. Pour sauce over chicken and bake 350° for 1 hour or 200° for 2 hours.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat egg.
Combine with milk and butter and stir into dry ingredients.
Add corn; fry in oil until browned on both sides.
Makes 15 to 20 small fritters.

title: layered banana pudding
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine flour and brown sugar; stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly; cook and stir 1 minute more.
Remove from the heat.
Gradually stir about 1 cup hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return all to the saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Remove from the heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool to room temperature, stirring occasionally.
Fold in the whipped cream. Layer a third of the pudding in a 2 quart glass bowl.
Top with half the bananas.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining pudding. Cover and chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Break eggs in a bowl; beat lightly.
Add remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Stir well.
Place pecans in pie shell.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Place egg, pizza sauce, salt, pepper and cornflakes in large mixing bowl, beat until all are combined.
Add ground beef, onion and mushrooms.
Mix together.
Press 1/2 of meat mixture in bottom of ungreased 9x9x2 pan.
Place 2 slices of mozzarella cheese over meat.
Press remaining meat mixture over cheese.
Bake in a 350 degree oven about one hour, or until meat begins to brown and shrink from sides of pan.
Cut remaining cheese in narrow strips and place over top of loaf.
Return to oven again for 3 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hacienda rice surprise
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth.
Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mt. olympus bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add onion.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes.
Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Spread 1/2 in greased 8 inch square baking dish.
Top with meat mixture.
1/2 parmesan cheese and remainder of dinner.
Melt margarine in sauce pan over low heat.
Blend in flour, gradually add milk, cook stirring constantly over low heat until thickened.
Stir small amount into eggs.
Return to hot mixture.
Pour over dinner.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 350° 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery and grapes in a large bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, preserves and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture and gently mix.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: seasoning mixture
directions: Mix together.
Pour into a salt shaker or a clean spice jar with a shaker top.
Use at table instead of salt.

title: refrigerator roll dough
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm. Measure into bowl 1 cup warm water and sprinkle in yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Stir in lukewarm water mix, egg and flour.
Mix well. Knead until smooth.
Place in refrigerator until double in bulk or until ready to use.
Can refrigerate up to a week.
Shape and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rye bread dip(for vegetables or chips)
directions: Mix ingredients and serve with rye bread.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix together cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten eggs and sugar, then add butter and milk.
Mix together well and pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour and salt.
Add slightly beaten eggs. Slowly add milk until mixture is of desired consistency.
Add shortening and onions.
Mixture should be semi-firm, not soupy.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together; shake.
Drain all liquid from beans.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and chill in refrigerator overnight.
Serve cold.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 2 cups hot water.
Set aside.
Mix 1 (8 ounce) package cream cheese with 1 cup hot water.
Set aside.
Mix Jell-O mixture and cream cheese mixture; fold in Cool Whip.
Add crushed pineapple and pecans.
Can be molded or leave in dish.
If molded, turn out on lettuce leaf and garnish with whipped cream and cherries.
Makes a very pretty and delicious dish.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt all ingredients, except nuts, in a 200° oven for 20 minutes.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper, then let cool

title: millionaire pie
directions: Add all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust and chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: sour cream nut horns
directions: Sift flour; cut in margarine as for pie dough.
Add yeast, egg yolks and sour cream.
Mix well (use your hands).
Chill dough 4 hours or overnight.
Work with small portions of dough; leave the rest in the refrigerator.
Pinch off a piece the size of walnut. Press with tips of fingers in 1 heaping teaspoonfuls of sugared mixture to form a 3-inch circle; turn over.
Do both sides until all sugar mixture is absorbed.
Roll like jelly roll; form into crescents.
Bake on greased pan at 325° for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Remove horns immediately; they stick to pan if let to cool.
Place on cake rack to cool.
Makes approximately 50.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes until done, drain and mash. Add other ingredients. Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad with topping
directions: Dissolve lemon and orange Jell-O in boiling water; stir well. Add cool water and stir again.
Add banana, nuts, pineapple and marshmallows.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, butter, peanut butter. Pour over cereal and mix good. Sprinkle powdered sugar over cereal and chocolate
till well coated.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In large bowl, place broccoli, onion, raisins, walnuts and bacon; toss.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Whisk together and pour over salad.
Chill.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Heat water and sugar; set aside and add fruit.
Melt oleo in bottom of pan.
Lay 1 pie crust in pan, then add fruit mixture. Cover with other pie crust.
Bake at 350° or until crust browns.

title: delicious corn bread
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and corn meal.
In a bowl, mix egg, milk and butter.
Add flour mixture; mix until moistened.
Pour into pan. Bake 30 minutes.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients and marinate overnight in covered bowl.
Make sure you drain all your beans.

title: spinach bake
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix with sour cream and onion soup mix and put in casserole.
Sprinkle croutons over top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: frankie's grandma urestis' banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, vanilla and banana flavoring.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture, one at a time.

title: mini sausages
directions: Place sausages and wine in a bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Combine all ingredients in a saucepan or electric skillet.
Heat to a slow boil for 5 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: almost pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Place in greased 3-quart baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes (approximately 2 cups). Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: olive puffs
directions: Cream margarine and sharp cheese; work in flour and paprika with hands.
Chill dough 15 to 20 minutes for easier handling. Mold 1/2 teaspoon dough around dry olive.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: festive fruitcake
directions: In a bowl mix marshmallows, orange juice, and milk; let stand, stirring occasionally while preparing remainder of fruitcake.

title: the best caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Stir constantly; pour over warm popcorn.
May make popcorn balls or eat unformed.
This is good over bagged buttered popcorn.

title: no knead rich egg batter bread
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cup flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl.
Gradually add water to dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add eggs and butter and 1/2 cup flour, beat 2 minutes at high speed.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Cover, let rise until double, about 35 minutes.
Stir down.
Turn into 2 well greased 1 1/2 quart casseroles.
Cover, let rise until double, about 40 minutes.
Bake in 375 degree oven for 35 minutes or until done.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Pour apple cider into crock-pot.
Add red hots; stir.
Cover; turn crock-pot on high.
Heat until cider is hot and red hots have melted.
Serve hot!

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain. In a large bowl, mix margarine and Parmesan cheese. Add egg. Add spaghetti and toss. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Spread cottage cheese over spaghetti. Brown meat, onion, green pepper and garlic. Drain. Stir in sauce, oregano and sugar. Pour over cottage cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Then top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni. Bake 10 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli in small amount of water until tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter or oil.
Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together and turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add 1 3/4 cups water to jello.
When partially set, add fruit and nuts.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in large, greased casserole.

title: pineapple brown betty
directions: Place half the drained pineapple in casserole.
Combine bread crumbs, sugar and cinnamon, sprinkle half this over fruit.
Dot with butter.
Repeat layers, sprinkle with grated lemon peel. Pour pineapple syrup over all.
Bake in moderate hot oven at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheeseburger bake
directions: Prepare Kraft macaroni and cheese as directed.
Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; add to macaroni and cheese.
Add milk and shredded cheese to mixture.
Butter 2-quart casserole dish.
Put mixture in dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour at 325° or until cheese is melted.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Place sauteed vegetables in casserole in layers with artichokes.
Make as many layers as desired.
Pour mushroom soup over all.
Add 1/2 stick of margarine and sprinkle with pepper over top.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and dust with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until topping is bubbly or lightly browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed turkey breast
directions: Mix stuffing mix according to directions on box using cold water (no cooking).
In a greased casserole, fold turkey slices in half and put tablespoon of stuffing inside.
Continue until all slices are used.
Leftover stuffing is placed between and around slices.
Cook 25 minutes at 375°.
Cover with mushroom soup and cook for 10 to 15 minutes more.
Serve hot.

title: cheese filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Mix remainder of ingredients together.
Add about 1 large teaspoon of this mixture on top of each cupcake and bake as usual for cupcakes.
Mixture will settle inside of cupcake.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer all day.
Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together lemon juice, whipped cream and milk.
Place the vanilla wafers on the bottom, then the mixture.
Layer it until you run out.
Chill and eat.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: In medium bowl, soften cream cheese.
Chop olives with pimentos and stir in cream cheese.
Chop nuts and mix until well blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: apple pie (microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Turn into pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Set pie on wax paper in oven.
Microwave at High for 14 to 18 minutes or until apples are tender, rotating 1/4 turn every 6 minutes, then every 3 to 4 minutes.

title: bernie's banana bread
directions: Spray a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vegetable and baking spray oil.
Mix corn oil, sugar, eggs, bananas and raisins until creamy in bowl.
Slowly add flour while continuing to mix banana mixture.
Add chopped pecans and orange juice; mix together.
Stir for approximately 1 minute.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until golden brown and a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool, then serve.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit thoroughly. Cream cheese until smooth. Beat in sugar. Add whipped cream and gently stir until smooth. Add all the fruits and marshmallows. Mix well and chill overnight before serving.

title: cream puff cake
directions: Bake at 375° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake as sheet cake.
Follow directions on box.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Use punch bowl or other large bowl.
Crumble cake in medium size pieces.
Put layer of cake, pineapple, pudding, strawberry filling and Cool Whip. Continue layering until all products are used.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: easy slice party cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour pan.
Beat mix, water, eggs and sour cream on low speed.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool for 10 minutes and invert to cool.

title: pasta carbonara
directions: Beat eggs with cream until smooth.
Cook pasta to al dente stage.
Immediately drain well and return to hot pan.
Add margarine and ham.
Toss together until margarine is melted and add egg mixture and cheese.
Toss together until well blended.
Serve immediately.

title: welfare cookies
directions: Boil sugar and syrup for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Stir well.
Add corn flakes.
Drop on wax paper.

title: cloud nine salad
directions: Add cream cheese and sugar together. Fold in pineapple, cherries and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip. Chill several hours before serving.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa; cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: orange cake filling
directions: You will also need a large piece of cardboard, aluminum foil, one stalk of large silk flowers (colors of your choice), 2 (9-inch) cake pans and 1 (12-inch) large round cake pan.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Mix all other ingredients together and place in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: summer vegetable medley
directions: Layer zucchini, onion and tomatoes in a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix together soy sauce, salt, garlic salt, pepper and margarine and pour over vegetables.
To with 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in beaten eggs.
Roll in bread crumbs and brown in olive oil.
Place chicken in baking dish and cover with tomato sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
If desired, may sprinkle with sauteed mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and vegetable shortening; add sugar.
Beat well. Add eggs one at a time; beat well.
After each egg, add flour slowly, butter flavoring and bottle of 7-Up; mix.
Bake 1 hour and 35 minutes in a 325° oven in Bundt pan or angel food pan can be used, but do not turn upside-down to cool.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13 baking pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix and pecans on top. Dot with margarine on top of this. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serve at room temperature with whipped topping.

title: apple burritos
directions: Put pie filling by spoonfuls in tortillas and roll up.
Place seam side down in glass baking dish.
Mix together the sugar, oleo, vanilla, water and cinnamon.
Heat until melted and pour over the tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Spread peanut butter with a knife on one slice of bread. Spoon jelly onto one slice of bread and spread around.
Put together with a squish and cut in half.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Serve chilled with raw vegetables such as cauliflower, celery, carrots, radishes, etc.
Keep refrigerated.

title: charlotte's green pickled tomatoes
directions: Soak tomatoes in pickling lime and 2 gallons of water for 24 hours.
Do not use aluminum pot.
Drain, then soak for four hours in water.
Change water every hour.

title: susmalainen pannukakku(finnish pancake)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put heavy frying pan or glass baking dish, 10 1/2-inches wide by 3-inches deep into oven for 10 minutes. Puffs as it cooks, falls as it cools.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dutch crumb apple pie
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Mix water and oil until thick (about 2 minutes).
Pour over mixture and work into a ball.
Press dough into pie pan.

title: asparagus salad with balsamic vinaigrette
directions: Place vinegar, shallots, chopped garlic and thyme in metal bowl.
Slowly whisk in the oil.
Season with salt and pepper and place in medium saucepan.
Set aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease dish.
Pour in rice.
Put chicken in and pour soup mixed together over the chicken.
Bake at 300° for about 2 hours.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 50 minutes longer.
Take out when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; beat in egg.
Stir in molasses. Sift dry ingredients into mixture.
Add water.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and save 1 cup broth.
Mix tomatoes and soup in bowl.
In pan, put layer of chips, layer of chicken and 1/2 of soup mixture; repeat the layers, then top with Cheddar cheese and pour 1/2 to 1 cup chicken broth.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: fruit dip
directions: Heat in microwave and blend together cream cheese and marshmallow cream.
Add food coloring.
Great with bananas, apples, pineapple and any fruit you like.

title: garlic and herb potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in medium saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine yogurt, mayonnaise, mustard, garlic, basil and thyme; blend well.
In a medium bowl, combine potatoes, yogurt mixture and radishes.
Toss lightly.
Serve warm.
Yields 4 servings.
Low-fat and cholesterol.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onions, garlic and oregano in large pot; drain. Add salsa, tomato paste and can of water.
Simmer 20 minutes. Drain corn and add to mixture.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Turn mixture off and let stand.
Mix (with fork) cottage cheese, eggs, salt and pepper in a bowl.

title: tomato slices(italian style)
directions: Spread tomatoes on platter and season with oil, vinegar, onion powder, black pepper and Adobo.
Top with oregano and grated cheese.
Let stand for an hour at room temperature before serving.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Combine all ingredients except marshmallows.
Mix well.
Pour into 10 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put marshmallows on top of hot cake and let stand while you prepare frosting.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryer as for frying.
Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in flour.
Arrange in an oblong pan or baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup melted butter or oleo over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: porcupine meatballs(oven meatballs)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine beef, rice, salt, pepper, Italian herb seasoning and onion.
Shape into meatballs and place in a 2-quart casserole.

title: easy caramel dip
directions: Melt caramels in microwave.
Stir in cream cheese until smooth.
Serve warm with fresh apple slices.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in a jar.
Add 1 to 2 teaspoons per hot cup of water.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Combine flour and sugar; add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla flavoring.
Mix until smooth.
Preheat electric griddle or electric skillet to 350° to 400°.
Cook about 1 minute on each side.
Serve with syrup, jam or honey.
Makes about 6 to 8 pancakes.

title: almond chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice, using package directions.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Saute chicken and mushrooms in saucepan along with margarine.
Arrange over rice.
Pour mixture of milk and soups over chicken.
Top with cheese and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: 1930's casserole
directions: Saute ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain.
Mix in a casserole with remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: glazed onions and carrots
directions: Place carrots in large saucepan with 1-inch boiling water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add onions.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until tender.
Drain water and add margarine, sugar, ginger and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, for 5 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bacon (cook bacon first because it takes longer to get crisp.)
Mix and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peter pan choco surprises
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Beat in eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients; chill dough 30 minutes. Wrap 1 teaspoon dough around each kiss. Bake on ungreased pan at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Let cool slightly. Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 70 cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon).
Add wet ingredients (oil, eggs, water, sugar and pumpkin).
Mix well by hand.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 3 loaves.

title: pan de jamon(ham bread)
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
In a separate container, mix yeast, sugar and warm milk.
Let it stand for 10 minutes.
Add the corn oil to the liquid mixture.
Mix, then add the flour mixture.
Stir well and knead until smooth.
On a floured surface, roll the dough to a rectangular shape (as in making a jelly roll).
Place the ham, raisins and olives over the dough, then roll like a jelly roll.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake in 400°
oven until golden brown.
Slice and serve.

title: hot pink lemonade
directions: Combine in kettle and heat to boiling. Pour into mugs and serve with a cinnamon stick.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: In a 2 quart microwave safe dish, place onions and cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave for 2 minutes on high, until onions are soft.
Add beans, brown sugar, catsup and mustard.
Mix well.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave at high for 6 minutes stirring once.
Uncover and continue to microwave on high for another 6 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: fancy chicken log
directions: Beat together first 3 ingredients. Blend in next two and 2 tablespoons parsley. Refrigerate remaining parsley. Shape into log. Wrap in plastic and chill 4 hours or longer. Coat with parsley and almonds. Serve with crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise together. Add lemon juice and mix. Add chicken, celery and water chestnuts. Top with margarine and crackers which have been mixed together. Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.

title: yummy chocolate squares
directions: Grease 8-inch square pan with butter.
Melt marshmallows, chocolate and butter in pan on stove.
Stir with a wooden spoon. Take from heat and mix.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Press mixture into greased pan.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Cut into pieces and serve.

title: divinity
directions: In a saucepan mix the first 4 ingredients.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cook to 260° (hard ball stage).

title: salsa steak
directions: Trim fat from meat and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cut into 4 to 6 serving size pieces. In a large skillet brown meat in hot oil. Transfer
to a 2 qt. square baking dish. In same skillet, cook and stir mushrooms, bell peppers

and onions oven medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes or until tender. Add more oil if needed. Stir in tomato sauce and chili powder. Cook until bubbly. Pour tomato mixture over the meat in the baking dish. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to
1 hour until meat is tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: poor man's chocolate cake
directions: Blend together the first 5 ingredients, then add remaining liquid ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350°.
Makes one 9 x 11-inch or three 8-inch round or lots of cupcakes.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: moroccan carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook in boiling salted water until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter in the hot pot.
Add almonds and cook over medium-low heat, stirring, until light gold, about 3 minutes.
Add carrots, cinnamon, cumin, cayenne and 1 teaspoon salt. Cook, stirring, over low heat until most of the liquid has evaporated and carrots are shiny and glazed, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients except for lime.
Squeeze lime over mixture and mix again.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: kraut dogs
directions: Place desired number of hot dogs in individual foil wraps. Sprinkle with sauerkraut, soup mix, chili sauce and 2 tablespoons beer or cola.
Seal and cook on grill.
Turn into toasted buns.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well and serve.

title: liver italian style
directions: Flour liver and saute until brown.
Remove, then saute onion. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water.
Add to onion, along with flour, to make gravy.
Add sage, parsley, salt and pepper until well blended.
Finally, return liver, along with cooked ham. Simmer all together for approximately 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in loaf pans at 325° for one hour.

title: louisiana brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in a large mixer bowl of mixer and beat on cake mix speed for 2 minutes.
Put in jelly roll pan that has been sprayed with Pam and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Frost while still hot with icing.

title: cherry delight
directions: For crust, mix graham cracker crumbs, butter, and 3 Tbsp. sugar and sprinkle small amount of vanilla in it.
Press in 9 x 13 greased dish and chill.
Mix powdered sugar and Dream Whip, then add cream cheese.
Spread on crust.
For topping, mix 1 can cherry pie filling and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread on Dream Whip layer.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: mushroom croissants
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix in mushrooms and Tony's Creole to taste.
Spread this mixture over croissant rolls and then roll up. Brush with egg white and sprinkle with peppercorns.
Then bake per package directions.

title: christmas cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and add to juice water to make 1 1/2 cups. Combine with cranberries in saucepan and cook until cranberries stop popping.
Add pineapple tidbits, diced orange sections and sugar.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Pour hot mixture over dry gelatin and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add pecans and pour into glass Pyrex dish.
Chill until set.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix the mayonnaise with the cream cheese. Pour over vegetables and mix together. Flavor is best if this is prepared the day before and stored overnight in the refrigerator.

title: rum coffee
directions: Pour hot coffee over ice cream; add honey to whipped cream. Fold into coffee-ice cream mixture.
Add rum and crushed ice. Makes about 2 quarts.

title: clam stuffed zucchini
directions: Scoop out zucchini meat.
Add all ingredients.
Add enough clam juice to hold mixture together.
Set zucchini close together in a greased baking dish.
Pile mixture into zucchini.
Spoon 2 tablespoons melted butter over all.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 6 stuffed zucchini servings.

title: cantaloupe and blackberry salad
directions: Cut cantaloupe into wedges or rings; scoop out seeds and fiber from center and peel.
Wash and drain blackberries.
Arrange wedges or rings of melon on lettuce and fill center with blackberries.
Serve with Lime-Honey Dressing (see Dressings).

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Make two layers in order in which ingredients are listed.
Put cherries and nuts on top.
(Use a punch bowl because the recipe makes a lot.)

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: In large pan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add cocoa, sugar and milk.
Whisk until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture begins to boil.
Time for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from
heat.
Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Add oats and mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° in oven for 15 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cook thoroughly.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Blend cake mix, Crisco oil, sour cream and eggs together for 10 minutes.
Will be thick.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Save 3 teaspoons sugar mixture; put aside.
Add rest of sugar and cinnamon to batter.
Add chopped nuts last.
Pour batter into ungreased 2 piece tube pan.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over cake.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and shortening; cream well.
Add mashed bananas and milk.
Beat well and add dry ingredients, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased 5 x 10-inch oblong or 2 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve plain with confectioners sugar sprinkled on top or with chocolate icing.

title: eggs souffle
directions: Trim crusts and butter 4 slices of bread and place, buttered side down, in dish.
Put cheese on each slice and 1/2 the ham. Butter other 4 slices of bread and place buttered side up.
Place cheese and rest of ham on top.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour mixture over bread slices.
Refrigerate until ready to bake.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy ziti casserole
directions: Pour cooked ziti into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown beef and onion; pour over it.
Top with spaghetti sauce, cheese and pepperoni. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken with apples
directions: Salt and pepper both sides of chicken and place on a rack in a shallow open roasting pan. Bake in hot oven (450°) until browned, about 20 minutes, then reduce oven to 350°. Remove chicken and rack; pour off any fat from pan. Return chicken to pan. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Pour over chicken along with apple juice. Stir in green beans. Cover and bake 25 minutes. Stir in apples. Cover and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Blend together cream cheese and Ricotta cheese.
Sprinkle gelatin over water and orange juice in small saucepan.
Soften 1 minute.
Heat and stir constantly until dissolved.
Add gelatin mixture, strawberry extract and Equal to cheese mixture and blend until smooth.
Fold in fruit.
Prepare whipped topping and fold into cherry mixture.
Pour into prepared pie crust and chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: mocha coffee
directions: Mix all together.
Store in jar.
To make one cup, use 2 or 3 teaspoons and fill with hot water.

title: 30 minute apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce, sugar and vinegar; boil hard for 20 minutes. (May boil longer if you want thicker butter.)
Add candy hearts and cook 10 more minutes.
Stir and pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Makes 5 pints.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll half the pastry and fit into pie pan.
Mix apple juice, tapioca, spices, salt and apples.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with a pie shell.
Make slit in top of crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 365° for 45 minutes.

title: steak fingers
directions: Pound steak to 1/4-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with lemon-pepper and salt.
Cut into 4 x 1/2-inch strips.
Dip steak in buttermilk.
Dredge in flour.
Brown steak on both sides in hot oil in a large skillet.
Drain well.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to 270°; add nuts. Boil to 295°. Take off burner quickly. Add butter and soda; hurry. Pour into 2 buttered cookie sheets.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350°.

title: hash brown pie
directions: Press hash browns into baking dish like pie shell.
Spoon 1/4 cup butter over hash browns.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Mix ham or sausage, green pepper and shredded cheese.
Pour mixture over pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Bake for 30 minutes more at 400°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs together.
Place in casserole and cover with bread crumbs.
Dot with oleo and bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: pineapple beet cake
directions: Blend ingredients in order given in large mixing bowl.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting or dust with powdered sugar.
This cake (a family favorite) is moist and keeps well.
We have had guessing games about this cake and no one ever guessed beets.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Fold Cool Whip into prepared pudding.
Crumble cookies in food processor.
Layer:
pudding, cookies, pudding, cookies.

title: strawberry angel treat
directions: In large bowl, add sugar to cheese; beat until fluffy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in cake.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread strawberry glaze with strawberries added over top.
(Fix strawberry mixture according to package.) Refrigerate.

title: lester's whole wheat bread
directions: Yeast may be added to dry ingredients.
Mix all together with enough whole wheat flour to make a rather stiff dough.
Let rise 1 to 2 hours.
Form into loaves and smear tops with grease.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven, after they have doubled in bulk.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, eggs and evaporated milk in medium bowl; mix well.
Add vanilla, cornmeal and cinnamon, stirring until well blended.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cool for 20 minutes before serving.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls(heritage recipe)
directions: Preheat oven 450 degrees.
Place yeast in bowl, add sugar, salt, milk, and add mashed potatoes and half of the flour.
Beat well.
Add softened shortening.
Reserve 1 c. flour for kneading dough.
Turn out on board and knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl, cover and place in refrigerator.
Take out as much as need. Shape in rolls.
Let rise in warm place until doubled.
Bake 15 - 20 minutes.

title: cannon ball cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed.
When cake is done, poke holes in cake and pour condensed milk over cake.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, butter and vanilla.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, 1 3/4 cups of sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with Carnation milk.
Mix 2/3 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle with
half of sugars and cinnamon mixture.
Pour in rest of batter.
Top with remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add sugar, egg and oil.
Add fruit, beans, vanilla and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water and oil in a large bowl.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan about 5 minutes. Prick cake with cake tester or wooden spoon, gradually spoon glaze over cake.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes(enough for two)
directions: Sift flour with sugar and salt.
Add milk.
Stir until smooth. Add egg and beat thoroughly.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: chocolate cream cheese dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix together the flour, melted butter and chopped pecans.
Cover bottom of a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° until light brown. Cool for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Spread pineapple in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cheese together.
Spread over pineapple.
Toss crackers with margarine and spread over cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peach punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water. Add remaining ingredients, except 7-Up, and freeze for 2 days (use gallon water jugs). Four hours before party, thaw to slush stage and add 7-Up.

title: mem's hamburg soup
directions: Spray Pam in a medium size pan.
Fry onion and then add hamburg and brown.
Cover the mixture with water (this will make your broth). After about 15 minutes, add the noodles.
When noodles are almost done, add the tomatoes and your soup is ready.

title: myers chocolate cake
directions: Mix everything at one time.
Put coffee in last.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350°.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish apple nut pie
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients one at a time. Pour into a greased pie tin. Sprinkle top with the cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: broccoli, cauliflower and carrot casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, cauliflower and carrots until barely done. Drain and place in casserole dish.
Combine mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and milk; heat until melted.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out of oven and pour onion rings over casserole.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Blend all ingredients until mixed. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello fruit mold
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to make 1 cup.
Boil and dissolve Jell-O in liquid.
Add to strawberries.
Stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and chill.

title: blueberry-rhubarb pie
directions: Prepare crust.
Combine blueberries (fresh or frozen) and rhubarb (fresh or frozen) in a bowl.
Add water.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add to berries-rhubarb mixture.
Stir well. Place in crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: parsonage open house pecans
directions: Put all 3 ingredients in iron frying pan and cook until water evaporates.
Crystals will form on nuts.
Pour nuts on baking sheets, distributing evenly.
Cook in preheated 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring after first 15 minutes.
Take out and let cool.

title: becky's macaroni and cheese
directions: In a saucepan melt butter over medium heat.
Add flour and cook, stirring for 3 minutes.
Whisk in warm milk and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add salt, pepper and cheese spread. Stir until cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile, bring water to a boil.
Add oil and salt.
Cook macaroni 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
Add macaroni to cheese sauce and stir. Pour into a 2-quart dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Top with shredded cheese and return to oven to melt cheese. Serves 8 to 10.

title: homemade hamburger helper
directions: In electric skillet, brown the hamburger.
Drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
In a saucepan, boil macaroni, drain and rinse.
Add macaroni to sauce.
Stir in grated cheese.
Place sliced cheese on top and allow to melt.
Eat and enjoy.

title: whole wheat raisin bread
directions: In saucepan, heat first 3 ingredients until lukewarm, 120° to 125°.
In large bowl, blend flour (white), yeast, salt and cinnamon.
Add eggs and warm liquid.
Beat 2 minutes with electric beater.
Stir in whole wheat flour, raisins and cherries.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed. Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
While cake is baking, melt in a double boiler the caramels with milk and butter.
(It is better to have this already prepared.)
When cake is done, pour caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips and 1/2 of the nuts over the cake and pour rest of the batter over this and sprinkle rest of nuts on top.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: quick and easy green beans with hamburger(soy sauce adds an oriental punch)
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in garlic, 1 1/2 cups water, the soy sauce and molasses; heat to boiling.
Add green beans and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: chocolate rice pudding
directions: Cook rice in little water until tender, add milk, salt, sugar and butter, and when nearly boiling add egg yolks beaten with cornstarch.
Mix with water or milk and cocoa; when thick enough, add flavor.
Beat egg whites with 6 tablespoons sugar and little flavoring, put over pudding and bake in slow oven until brown.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
In large mixing bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form, adding sugar gradually while beating. When smooth and shiny, add vanilla and food coloring.
Beat until well-blended.
Line 2 baking sheets with foil.
Spoon meringue onto foil.
Bake kisses for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until firm.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Add all ingredients and bake covered for 2 hours.

title: suckers
directions: Boil to 310°.
Remove from fire; add flavoring and color.
Pour into little cups.

title: pizza dough
directions: In a bowl add all ingredients except yeast mixture.
Add yeast mixture to dry ingredients and mix well.
Turn out onto floured pastry cloth and knead about 1 cup flour into the dough until it's firm, but not tough.
Roll out to desired shape (this much dough will make a crust big enough for a large institutional sized cookie sheet).
Place on well-oiled cookie sheet and let rise 15 minutes in a warm place.
Add your favorite pizza sauce, toppings and cheese.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
(I usually bake my pizza for 15 minutes and then add cheese for the last 10 minutes of baking time.)

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Peel potatoes, cut in medium-size chunks, and boil until tender while potatoes are boiling.
Slice sausage into 1/4-inch thick pieces, simmer them 15 minutes.
Drain excess liquid.
Drain most of the liquid off potatoes; leave some so potatoes won't be dry. Add oleo and sausage, mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: veal paprika
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Saute with veal (which has been cut into 1-inch cubes) and onion until golden brown.
Add salt, paprika and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer slowly until veal is tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Mix flour, cold water and sour cream and stir into veal.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Keep hot in a 300° oven or serve from chafing dish.
A garnish of toasted, slivered almonds add a nice touch.
I serve this over buttered noodles, sprinkled with poppy seed.

title: salmon dip
directions: Clean salmon and mash into a fine mixture.
Soften cream cheese.
Blend all ingredients together.
Sprinkle crushed pecans and parsley on top or form into ball and roll in parsley and pecans.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: mom's pumpkin raisin cookies
directions: Combine sugar, egg, oil, vanilla and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients. Stir in raisins. Drop by teaspoonful onto a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool for 2 minutes on pan.
Remove and put on paper to finish cooling.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked apple pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix together flour and milk.
Then add eggs and sugar; mix.
Pour batter over top of melted butter.
Add apples and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until pancake puffs and turns a little golden.
Serves 2 hungry people!

title: pumpkin - pecan bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in bowl. Beat in eggs. Add pumpkin and 2/3 cup water, mixing well. Sift in dry ingredients, blending well. Stir in raisins and pecans. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix together.
Roll in small balls.
Flatten with fork on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
(Don't get too brown.)
Makes approximately 60.

title: white chocolate and cranberry cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugars and the egg.
Add the dry ingredients and brandy; stir well.
Add white chocolate chips and cranberries.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Best to take them out when they are still doughy.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: autumn fruitcake
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and baking powder.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
This will be a thick batter.
Pour into a loaf pan and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix margarine and peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
When it gets too stiff for mixer, finish mixing by hand.
Roll into little balls.
Melt wax and chocolate morsels in double boiler over low heat.
Cover balls with chocolate mixture by dipping.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: pizza dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a large (12-inch) plate.
Cover with entire bottle of chili sauce.
Add sliced black olives, sliced green olives, chopped onions, chopped green peppers or other vegetable favorites.
Cover with finely grated Mozzarella cheese. Keep refrigerated.
Serve with crackers or corn chips.

title: imitation crab quiche
directions: Melt margarine in Dutch oven over medium-low heat.
Add flour; stir frequently, allowing flour to cook for 10 minutes.
Flour may turn light gold, but should not brown.
Chop fine in food processor:
parsley, onion, celery and garlic.
Chop green onion bottoms with knife; snip tops with scissors.
Add chopped vegetables to roux.
Stir to blend, then cover and simmer until wilted.
Add water slowly, while stirring to blend.
Add rest of ingredients, except shrimp.
Simmer, covered, for at least 30 minutes.
Check frequently to be sure gravy doesn't stick.
Add water if needed.

title: taco twist
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato sauce and green pepper.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat; set aside.
Combine noodles, 1/2 cup cheese and sour cream.
Place on bottom of casserole dish.
Top with meat mixture and rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Place 1/2 of crumb mixture in an 8-inch square pan.
Cover with the cranberry sauce.
Top with the other half of the crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Cool Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions 5 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream, squash and onions together.
Mix stuffing and butter, keeping two or three tablespoons of dry stuffing mix for topping. Mix all together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 325° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix together peanut butter and Marshmallow Fluff.
Boil 5 minutes the sugar, milk and butter.
Mix peanut butter and Fluff with sugar, milk and butter after boiling.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and marinate chicken wings overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not turn over.

title: raspberry - applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce just to boiling.
Add Jell-O and mix well. Stir in thawed raspberries.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch ring mold. Chill until set.
Unmold onto lettuce covered plate.
Serve with sour cream or whipped cream-mayonnaise dressing.
Serves 6.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Mix cream cheese and cherry juice.
Fold in remainder of ingredients and chill.

title: pea salad
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan the lettuce first, then other ingredients (except sugar, mayonnaise and cheese) one at a time (save bacon until ready to serve).
Top with sugar and mayonnaise.
Then sprinkle on the cheese.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Crumble on bacon when ready to serve.
Mix in or serve as is.
