title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Place in casserole dish or an 11 x 9-inch pan. Layer with American cheese, crushed Pringles and slivered almonds. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients (including cocoa).
Add alternately with milk, starting and ending with flour.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except Cheddar in 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Cover and bake until it bubbles, approximately 30 minutes.
Remove the lid and let the top brown a little.
Let cool until it's comfortable to taste.
Serve with crackers (like Triscuits). Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Break up bread and put in casserole.
Brown sausage; drain off fat.
Put sausage on top of bread and sprinkle with cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper together.
Make sure eggs are well beaten.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: rich and charlie's salad
directions: Clean and cut up all ingredients. Put into a large bowl. Mix with oil and vinegar. Let stand for about an hour before you serve.

title: hershey's cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk.
Bring to a bubbly boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring to 234°, soft ball stage.
Bulb of candy thermometer should not rest on bottom of pan.
Remove from heat. Add butter or margarine and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Cool to 110°. Beat until fudge thickens and loses gloss.
Spread onto buttered 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Cool.
Yields 3 dozen squares.

title: layered tuna salad
directions: Layer lettuce, noodles, cucumbers, tomatoes, tuna, peas and cheese in 3-quart serving bowl.
Spread dressing over salad, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss to serve.
Serves 8.

title: rice pudding
directions: Simmer first three ingredients 20 minutes.
Add sugar.
Add milk and eggs at last.
Let sit.
Ready to serve 20 to 30 minutes.

title: saturday noodle bake
directions: Combine ground beef and onion.
Brown in butter.
Add soup, cheese, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles in salt and water, drain and place in baking dish.
Pour sauce over. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased casserole.
Add onions and return to oven for about 5 minutes.

title: e.s.p. cookies
directions: Mix together egg, sugar and peanut butter.
Make dough into balls, marble size.
Bake at 325° for 9 minutes.
Place chocolate kiss on each one and return to oven for 1 minute.
Makes 24 to 30 cookies.
With chocolate kisses, they taste like peanut butter cups.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Serves 30 to 40.

title: tuna seven seas casserole
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, water, salt, onion and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Pour half of mixture into a greased casserole dish.
Make 3 layers of Minute rice (from box), peas and tuna. Add remaining soup; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes; cut through mixture with knife after baking 10 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add egg and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour and M&M's.
Drop teaspoonfuls on greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Cool until set.

title: cottage cheese pie
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar.
Gradually add rest of ingredients except cheese.
Beat cheese until smooth.
Fold together all ingredients.
Turn into pie crust.
Bake at 300° until firm.

title: country-style yellow squash
directions: In 2-quart glass dish, place water, salt, squash and onion. Cover.

Microwave on High for 13 to 15 minutes, stirring after 7 minutes. Drain well and mash. To squash, add 1/2 of the crumbled bacon, butter, pepper, basil, bread cubes, cheese and sour cream. Mix well and place in lightly buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with remaining bacon. Cover.
Microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: catfish parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs, cheese, oil and seasonings.
Dip fish in egg/milk mixture and roll in crumb coating.
Arrange in lightly oiled baking pan and cook in 400° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or until flaky. Heart healthy!

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Melt caramel and evaporated milk in double boiler or in microwave on Low heat. Place 1/2 of cake batter in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over cooked batter.
Pour melted caramel mixture over all.
Drop rest of cake mix on.
Bake additional 15 minutes at 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer buttered bread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole pan. Sprinkle sausage evenly over bread slices.
Sprinkle on cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; blend well.

title: holiday fruit bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend bananas, eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture. Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: mexican chicken and squash casserole(calabaza con pollo)
directions: Stir and brown cut up chicken in oil in a deep pot for about 10 minutes.
Cut squash in small chunks; place over chicken.
Add chopped tomatoes over squash.
Add finely chopped garlic.
Pour canned corn over ingredients.
Add water and salt.
Cover tightly; simmer for about 30 to 35 minutes or until squash is tender.
For added flavor, you may use 1/2 cup tomato sauce and 1/2 bell pepper, sliced.
Serves 8 or more.

title: chocolate topping
directions: Melt in double boiler until thin, then coat mints and let set on wax paper until dry.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except last 3 and spoon into a greased 9 x 13 x 3-inch baking dish.
Top with the cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight. About 40 minutes before serving time, place in a 400° oven and cook for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Should nuts begin to get too brown, cover lightly with a piece of foil.
Be sure dish is hot through and through.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: quick and easy nut bread
directions: Mix.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before putting in loaf pan. Grease and lightly flour loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: liver and onions
directions: Cut liver in smaller slices (if desired).
Cover liver with flour; add butter to frying pan and place liver in pan.
Brown on both sides; add oregano and lemon.
Add water to cover liver; slice onions and place on top of liver.
Add salt and pepper. When water cooks down to gravy consistency, it's done!

title: mexican corn muffins(reduced-fat)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray muffin cup with no-stick spray. In large bowl, stir together the cornmeal, flour, sugar and baking powder.
In a small bowl, stir together egg whites, buttermilk and applesauce.
Add the buttermilk mixture to flour mixture and stir until moistened.
Fold in chili peppers and 3/4 cup of cheese. Fill muffin cups about 3/4 full with batter.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes or until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: sweet potato souffl
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, 1/2 cup butter and vanilla. Place into a 2 quart dish. Melt remaining butter and set aside. In separate bowl, mix pecans, flour and brown sugar together. Stir in melted butter. Pour over sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: upton's best clam chowder
directions: Brown first four ingredients.
Add chicken broth, clam juice, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes, corn and clams.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
In a separate pan melt and blend in butter and flour.
Slowly add half and half. Whip smooth and add to soup, cook 10 minutes.
Delicious with your favorite corn bread and honey.

title: royal blueberry pie
directions: Line pie shell with 2 cups of berries.
To make sauce, cook remaining berries, sugar, cornstarch, salt and water over medium heat until thickened.
Remove and add butter.
Cool.
Pour over berries and chill until served.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: grandma grace's baked cheesecake(won "honorable mention" in a cooking contest)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Line an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan with the crescent rolls.
Pinch dough together to seal seams. Pour filling on top.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Whip refried beans; spread over shallow baking dish.
Mash avocados.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Smooth over bean layer.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning. Spread over avocado layer.
Add remaining ingredients in progressive layers.
Refrigerate at least one hour.

title: creamy french dressing
directions: In a blender, place the mayonnaise, ketchup, vinegar, sugar, onion, salt and pepper; cover and process until smooth.
While processing, gradually add oil in a steady stream.
Refrigerate. Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix margarine, flour and nuts.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan; press into place.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Blend cream cheese and Cool Whip (reserve some for topping). Spread over crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Put this over cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and garnish with nuts if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: ultimate oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butters with sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir flour with baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Fold in while and milk chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop my rounded tablespoons about 2-3-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9-11 minutes.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sour cream cucumber salad
directions: Slice cucumbers thinly.
Mix all ingredients together and serve.
Serves 5.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread on deep plate and top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with taco chips.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, placing whites in a large bowl and yolks in another large bowl.
Let egg whites warm to room temperature, about 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 300° and grease a 10-inch tube pan.

title: merv's dip
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients in a saute pan.
Add next 3 ingredients into a crock-pot.
(Cut Velveeta into chunks to melt easier.)
Drain meat mixture after browning and add to crock-pot mixture.
Let simmer until cheese is melted.

title: banana chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add bananas, vanilla, eggs and sour cream.
Sift together dry ingredients and add.
Mix well by hand. Add chocolate chips (more than 1/2 cup can be used if desired). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pickled black-eyed peas
directions: Heat all ingredients, except peas and onions.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over peas and onions, which have been mixed together in a bowl.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Combine sugar, flour and 8 tablespoons of reserved pineapple juice; mix well.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix all well. Pour into a 1-quart greased casserole.
Combine melted butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: surprise stew
directions: Put beef in slow cooker.
Combine other ingredients and blend. Pour over beef and cover.
Cook for 4 hours at medium setting. Don't stir and don't peek.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mexican meat dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together; drain.
Add all other ingredients, except shredded cheese.
Heat until warm.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch casserole pan.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese on top.
Put back into oven until cheese melts.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: white cake with pineapple filling
directions: Combine dry ingredients into bowl. Add shortening, milk and flavorings. Beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Add unbeaten egg whites and beat for 2 minutes on medium speed. Pour into 2 (9-inch) floured and greased pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 5 minutes. Cool on cake racks.

title: oriental wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients except wings in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add rings to sauce.
Stir to coat well. Remove wings from sauce.
Place on a foil-lined baking sheet. Bake wings for 20 to 30 minutes and brush with remaining sauce during the cooking period.
Serve with your favorite potato recipe (baked, fried, etc.).

title: spiced roast chicken(gore family recipe)
directions: Prepare stuffing:
In a large saucepan, heat olive oil.
Add onion and saute 2 minutes or until softened.
Stir in garam masala and cook 1 minute.
Add mushrooms, parsnips and carrots; cook, stirring 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in walnuts, thyme, bread crumbs, egg and salt and pepper.
Stuff and truss chicken. Place breast down in a roasting pan; add 1/4 cup water.
Roast 45 minutes; turn chicken breast up and dot with margarine.
Roast about 45 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted in thickest part of thigh (not touching bone) registers 185° (85°C).
Transfer to platter; keep warm.

title: veal marsala
directions: Season meat with Tex Joy steak seasoning.
Cook meat in 1/2 cup olive oil.
Add onions, bell peppers and mushrooms and cook until crisp, not mushy.
Add
wine
and, if needed, add a little water.
May need a clove of garlic.
Cook spaghetti and drain. Add grated Italian cheese and pour sauce over spaghetti.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Toss gently with everything, except almonds.
Chill several hours (better overnight) before serving.
Sprinkle almonds on top before serving.
Can be used as is on lettuce or put in pineapple boats.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut cooked potato in half. Scoop out insides, trying not to tear the skin. Mix the potatoes, salt and pepper and the broccoli and cheese. Restuff back into the potato skin.

title: petite cherry cheesecake
directions: Place wafers in bottom of each cupcake paper.
Fill 2/3 full of mixture, made of first five ingredients.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with cherry pie filling and refrigerate or may be topped with other fruit, preserves, nuts or chocolate.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, salt, pepper, minced garlic and Italian seasoning.
Drain.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce and Prego. Simmer until well blended.
Remove from heat and let it set.
When ready to serve, heat and serve over spaghetti noodles.
Garlic bread and a green salad make an excellent meal.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pat over top of casserole.
Bake 40 to 60 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix together flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Mix beaten egg and milk in separate bowl.
Coat chicken with seasoned flour.
Dip in beaten egg mixture and coat again with seasoned flour.
Fry chicken in oil of your choice until fully cooked over medium-low heat.
Drain on absorbent paper towels.

title: chicken breasts in cream cheese sauce
directions: Soften 1 stick butter.
Add chives, about 2 tablespoons or to your liking.
Stuff breasts, fold.
Dip breasts in melted butter. Season with salt and pepper.
Roll in corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° until done and golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: "mageritsa" - traditional easter soup
directions: With electric mixer, beat eggs until thick and foamy; add lemon juice and continue beating until well blended.
Slowly add about 2 cups hot broth to the beaten eggs and lemon mixture, stirring constantly.
Return sauce to saucepan and simmer for 5 minutes longer, shaking pan in a back-and-forth motion.
Garnish with parsley or croutons.
Serve hot.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package.
Bake in greased 9-inch pie plate 40 minutes or until done.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Scoop out center of brownie, using a spoon, leaving 1-inch crust around edge and thin layer of brownie on bottom; reserve brownie scraps.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in segments (discard wing tips).
Fry 24 pieces in hot oil, approximately 10 minutes (do not flour chicken) until brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: pueblo beef and rice casserole
directions: Cook and drain ground beef.
In a large bowl combine rice, meat, tomatoes, onion, spices and taco seasoning mix.
In a small bowl combine sour cream, olives and green chiles.
Use a 9 X 13 pan and layer 1/2 of the beef/rice mixture, 1/2 sour cream mix, and 1/2 cheese.
Repeat.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 45 minutes.

title: garlic dip
directions: Combine ingredients in blender; blend well.
Chill overnight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine sugar with oil.
Add eggs and beat.
Add pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good with a cream cheese frosting.

title: party sandwich loaf
directions: Cut crust from loaf of bread.
Cut loaf into 3 or 4 slices lengthwise.
Spread cream cheese or butter on each layer.
Then spread a layer of chicken salad, a layer of tomatoes and onions and a layer of egg salad garnished with slices of pimentos or anchovies.
(Any favorite salad combination may be substituted, however, a colorful middle layer is very attractive when loaf is sliced.
All the layer fillings should be spread thickly.)
Chill loaf and place on a platter.
Cover loaf on all sides with cream cheese as if icing a cake.
Add your choice of food coloring to remaining cream cheese and put into pastry tube and decorate loaf with flowers and leaves or writing if you prefer.
Decorate bottom of loaf where it meets the plate as well.
Chill loaf overnight and before serving, slice and serve with tossed salad.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients (except cheese).
Pour half of mixture in greased pan.
Spread cheese over that and cover with remaining mixture.
Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda, nuts and salt.
Shape dough by rounded teaspoonful into balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll ball in mixture.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: santa fe super chief's french toast
directions: Beat eggs with cream and salt, blending well.
Place in a shallow dish and coat the bread slices thoroughly, turning to soak both sides through.
Fry until nicely browned in hot fat.

title: hootenanny cake
directions: Grease bottom of tube pan. Mix together cake mix, instant pudding, eggs, vanilla, salad oil, baking powder and water. Combine nuts, cinnamon and sugar in separate bowl.
Layer in pan as follows:
1/3 nut mixture, 1/2 batter, 1/3 nut mixture, remaining batter and remaining nut mixture. Bake at 350° until tested done.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Heat oysters; drain liquid into heated milk.
Combine in layers in a buttered casserole.
Begin and end with bread crumbs. Use enough liquid to make moist.

title: fudge filled bars
directions: Combine cake mix, melted butter and eggs to form a dough.
Pat 2/3 on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips, milk and butter over low heat.
Spread over cake mixture.
Add nuts.
Put rest of cake mixture between hands to form a thin layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: frosted grapes
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Dip small bunches of grapes into egg white and let stand on waxed paper until nearly dry.
Sprinkle with sugar and refrigerate until dry.
Best to keep them in a tightly closed container.
Use as a garnish.

title: yogurt jello
directions: Make jello with 1/2 cup less hot water.
Let cool to egg-white thickness.
Beat in yogurt.
Let set.
You do not taste the yogurt.
Can use any flavor jello or yogurt.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep refrigerated.
Serve with your favorite fish dish.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Place ingredients in blender.
Blend 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased, floured 9-inch deep pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine pumpkin, evaporated milk, eggs, sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt in a large bowl.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture.
Top with pecans.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Shape into strawberries and roll in red sugar.
Place a green tinted almond piece to make the stem.

title: selah's holiday leftover casserole
directions: In 2-quart shallow casserole, arrange broccoli; top with turkey.
Combine soup, milk and pepper.
Pour over turkey.
Crush crackers coarsely.
Mix with cheese and paprika.
Sprinkle over turkey.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, or until hot and bubbling. Serves 4. Can be doubled.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix 4 cups corn flakes with 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Put on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve warm from oven.

title: gala punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well just before serving.
May use any color Kool-Aid.

title: banana milkshake
directions: Add ingredients in blender with ice and crush.

title: lemon rounds
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until smooth.
Beat in eggs, lemon peel and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, stir together the flour, salt and soda.
Stir into the margarine mixture.
Then stir in oats, dates and nuts until combined.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 18 minutes or until dry in center and edges are well browned.

title: bubble's beef stew
directions: Brown roast slowly in a little oil with onion.
Add bouillon, pinch of parsley, thyme and oregano.
Add tomato and celery (diced).
Add potatoes, carrots, Veg-All, corn and peas to 1 pack of brown gravy.
Thicken with flour.
Bring to a boil and simmer. Add soy sauce and mix together.

title: jenny's stone soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook about 6 to 8 hours, until vegetables are tender.
(Amounts and selection of vegetables may be changed depending on personal preference). Parents may want to remove the stone soon after starting the soup. It does not tenderize well.

title: peanut butter cookies 2
directions: Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add Bisquick and vanilla. Roll dough into balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes. As soon as cookies come out of the oven, press a kiss on the top.

title: liquados mexicanos
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes in blender. Strain liquid and serve.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Mix well and rub into meat wrapped in heavy foil.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning unwrap and pour 2 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce on meat.
Rewrap tightly.
Place in large pan.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours.

title: marinated crock-pot pot roast
directions: Place meat in bag.
Stir together all ingredients except last 4.
Pour over meat and refrigerate overnight, turning a couple of times.
Place onions and carrots in crock-pot.
Add roast and marinade.
Cover and cook at low setting for 10 hours.
Measure out 2 cups cooking liquid; pour into saucepan.
Add the water and flour mixture to cooking liquid and thicken for gravy.

title: cocoa fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. In large bowl, sift flour with sugar, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add shortening and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes longer.
Pour batter into pan; bake 35 to 40 minutes or until surface springs back when gently pressed with fingertip.
Cool completely and frost.

title: southern sausage bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In an 8-inch baking dish, drizzle 1 tablespoon sausage drippings. Prepare muffin mix as package directs using 1 egg and 1/3 cup milk.
Spread batter evenly in dish. Arrange sausages and peach slices on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg. Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes until golden brown. Serve
with butter, pancake syrup or honey.

title: dessert squares
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking pan melt oleo.
Spread cracker crumbs over oleo.
Spread coconut over cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over coconut.
Sprinkle walnuts over coconut.
Pour can of condensed milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: peanut butter meltaway cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a pan and cook over low heat until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, soda and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool good on counter.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, oil, margarine and eggs. Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop dough 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: shrimp in garlic butter
directions: Place butter in custard cup. Microwave at high 30-45 second, until melted. Stir in garlic powder and parsley flakes.

title: glazed strawberry pie
directions: Prepare pie shell.
Let cool.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, water and salt; mix well.
Add crushed strawberries; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add cut strawberries.
Cool; pour in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar and beat until thick.
Beat egg yolks and add remaining cup of sugar, beating until creamy.
Add Eagle Brand milk and cream to egg yolk mixture.
Brown pecans in margarine, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar.
Combine all mixtures.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer can and finish filling with regular milk.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Mix crushed cookies and melted butter; press in a long cake pan. Freeze for 15 minutes or until firm.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 30-45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: queen elizabeth cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates and add soda; let set until cool.
Cream butter or margarine; add sugar and stir until well mixed.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients and nuts and mix well.
Add the cooked dates and water.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 inch pan at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up first 4 ingredients.
Mix small amount of milk with Miracle Whip to make dressing.
Toss with vegetables.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Mix with salad just before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix cheese and margarine until smooth.
Spread mixture on first layer (1/2) of the bread slices in 8 x 13-inch or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Spread ham and mushrooms all over bread.
Place remaining bread slices on top.
Spread remaining half of cheese mixture on top.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over top of bread.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Just before baking, sprinkle paprika over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain; beat eggs.
Add milk, bread, sausage, cheese and seasoning.
Put in shallow baking dish.
Let set 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Blend 2 pkgs cream cheese.
Drain and crumble shrimp.
Add to cream cheese along with mustard.
Mix together.
Form into ball and roll into nuts.

title: royal ambassadors hamburger dinner
directions: Hamburger, salt and pepper to taste, make 1/4-inch patties for as many as needed.
Place on a sheet of foil large enough to fold over and seal patties.
On top of each patty, layer thinly sliced potatoes, carrots and onion.
Salt and pepper top of each patty and place a pat of butter on each.
Fold the foil and secure tightly.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 400°.
Use juice for gravy.

title: stuffed spinach pizza
directions: Let bread dough thaw and rise until doubled in size.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Divide risen dough into 1/3.
Pat 1/3 of dough into bottom of pie pan.
Toss spinach, mushrooms and onions; season with salt and pepper.
Layer half of Mozzarella cheese on top of dough; top with spinach mixture.
Layer with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Roll out 1/3 of dough to 9-inch circle.
Place on top of pizza.
Pinch together top and bottom crusts.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Spread pizza sauce over top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes. Cool.
Take the remaining dough and shape into bread sticks.
Let rise on greased baking sheet until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water.
Drain.
Mix soup, milk and salt and heat, stirring constantly.
Add
cheese, stir until melted.
Add
remaining
ingredients,
except
cup almonds and the crumbs.
Mix with noodles, put
in	buttered
2 quart casserole, top with crumbs and
remaining almonds.	Bake, uncovered, in hot 400° oven for about 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and shredded zucchini.
Mix all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Beat until moist.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jamaican jungle bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Add all at once the remaining ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
(Glaze if desired.)

title: summertime corn scramble
directions: Fry bacon in 19-inch skillet until crisp.
Drain, reserving fat.
Return 1 tablespoon fat to skillet.
Add corn and cook 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Stir in milk; simmer 2 to 3 minutes.
Add eggs, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until set. Serve topped with bacon and cheese.

title: noodles and turkey
directions: Brown onion, turkey and noodles seasoning packet with water. Let simmer about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: special thousand island dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill. Yield:
2 cups (about 13 calories per tablespoon).

title: empress chili
directions: Brown meat in a large, heavy pan.
Combine bay leaves and allspice in a bag or piece of clean cheesecloth.
Add with remaining ingredients to meat.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer over medium heat for 3 hours.

title: fat-free pineapple-carrot muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and salt in medium bowl.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually beat in apple juice concentrate, thawed, increasing mixer speed to high.
Fold in nonfat milk powder into whites, then fold in wheat or oat bran and flour mixture.
Stir in shredded carrots.
Spoon into 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups.
Top with drained pineapple.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean at 375°.
Cool on wire racks.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: frances' chicken casserole
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions, substituting chicken broth for water.
Saute onions and green pepper in butter. Mix all ingredients together and place in large dish (2 smaller dishes may be used).
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Mix together. Place in a casserole dish and bake in a 350 degree oven.

title: potatoes and frankfurters au gratin
directions: Make a white sauce with butter, flour, milk, salt and pepper. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Layer strips of bacon on top or chop and mix in beans.
Mix all ingredients into beans.
Pour in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini honey bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; stir in pecans.
Peel zucchini, if desired; shred enough zucchini to measure 2 cups. Combine zucchini and the remaining ingredients; add to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Let cool.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: peanut butter rice krispies bars
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until mixed.
Pour over Rice Krispies. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread mixture in pan and let cool.
May frost with chocolate icing.

title: brownies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: turkey croquettes
directions: Brown meat, breaking up large pieces; drain and let cool.
In a saucepan, melt butter and stir in flour (thick and pasty).
Pour in milk and blend with a whisk; cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add onion and seasonings and let cool.

title: impossible turkey pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie plate; put turkey, mushrooms, onions, salt and cheese in pie plate.
Beat rest of the ingredients until smooth, in blender at high speed. Pour into pie plate; bake until golden brown.
Insert knife into the center, should come out clean.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: seven layer taco salad
directions: Peel and pit avocados, then mash in medium-size bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, salad dressing and taco seasoning in a bowl.
Spread bean dip on bottom of dish and top with avocado mixture.
Layer with sour cream and taco mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Cut up rhubarb and put in cake pan.
Sprinkle on Jell-O and sugar.
Pour water over all.
Put dry cake mix on top.
Melt butter and pour over this.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: bernice's quick and easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together milk, flour and sugar.
Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour flour mixture over butter, but do not stir.
Add fruit and do not stir.
Bake at 350° until brown.
(Makes its own crust.)

title: spice tea
directions: Boil water with cinnamon and cloves; boil together for 5 minutes.
Steep bags of tea for 5 minutes.
Add frozen orange juice, lemon juice and sugar.

title: greek honeyed baklava
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar, honey, water and lemon juice. Simmer over medium heat until thick enough to coat back of spoon and amber in color (about 40 minutes). Set aside to cool.

title: grape chiffon pie
directions: In saucepan, stir gelatin into grape juice.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add sugar and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin and sugar are dissolved. Cool.
Stir in light cream. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold egg whites and whipped cream into gelatin.
Pour into pie shell. Cover with 1/2 cup grape jelly. Chill until firm.
Top with remaining grape jelly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn bread stuffing(makes 15 cups)
directions: Make square corn bread as directed on box (not muffins); cool. Crumble and set aside.
Prepare stuffing mix.
In a large bowl, combine mixes, celery and pecans.
Add beaten eggs and enough broth to moisten.
Use to stuff a chicken or turkey.
If desired, bake in a greased shallow baking dish, covered, for 45 minutes at 325° or until heated through.

title: sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix butter and powdered sugar until light and smooth.
Beat in egg and vanilla until fluffy.
In medium bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add in thirds to creamed mixture, blending after each addition.
Divide in half and flatten each.
Put in a dish and wrap.
Chill 1 1/2 hours.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: mini tart shells
directions: Mix margarine and cream cheese and blend well. Mix in flour and salt until it sticks together good.
Place in fridge until cold.
Pinch off small balls and press into ungreased muffin tins. Bake at 375° until slightly brown.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: apple-spice glazed ham
directions: Place ham slices on broiler rack.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar, applesauce and Old Bay seasoning.
Spread glaze over ham slices.
Garnish with pineapple slices and cherries.
Top pineapple slices with remaining glaze.
Broil 25 minutes.

title: almond punch
directions: Mix all together.
Can be chilled and served cold or heated and served warm.
It makes a great holiday punch when served this way.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add melted butter.
Mix flour and sugar.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: creamy broccoli chicken bake
directions: Place cooked and chopped broccoli and chicken in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Beat soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: *I use 3 teaspoons pumpkin pie spice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add all other items and sprinkle top with extra crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: macaroni pie
directions: First cook noodles. Drain water off and add butter until melted. Then add milk. Stir in beaten eggs and cut up cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in casserole sprayed with Pam for approximately 30 to 35 minutes in hot oven (350°). Do not overcook. To check and see if done, take a case knife and stick in middle of macaroni. If it looks congealed, it is done.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Put all ingredients except the 3 tablespoons butter into a large bowl and mix well.
Cover and chill 2 hours or more.
Shape into balls using about a tablespoon for each.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix egg, hamburger, chopped onion and chopped green pepper with 1/2 cup of flour, then fry until done.
After this is done, remove, then use the other 1/2 cup of flour to make gravy with water and the grease.
Put the steak back into the gravy for about 45 minutes to simmer.
Add salt and pepper to your taste.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork (dipped in sugar) to make crisscross.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: almond goodie dessert
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients
and toast in oven 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir every 5 minutes.
Cool.
Reserve 3/4 cup for topping.
Mix instant vanilla pudding with milk.
Add Cool Whip.

title: rice con queso
directions: Mix together rice, beans, garlic, onion and chilies.

In casserole repeat layers of rice-bean mixture, Ricotta cheese (thinned slightly with milk or yogurt) and shredded Jack cheese. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and garnish (if desired) with black olives, fresh onions and parsley.
End with layer of rice-bean mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. During the last few minutes of baking, sprinkle grated cheese over top.
Garnish. Serves 6.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease
and sugar Bundt cake pan (use sugar instead of flour).
Add sugar, oil and eggs to cake mix. Stir until well creamed.
Add sour cream, poppy seed and almond extract.
Beat well.
Bake 45
minutes to 1 hour in hot 325° oven (or until tested
"done" with a toothpick).
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in the other ingredients.
Put in greased and floured 8 x 4 x 4-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs; combine with sugar.
Pour hot milk slowly over mixture.
Add salt and vanilla.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce heat to 250° and bake until firm.

title: chocolate candy cookies
directions: Bring to a boil the oleo, sugar, milk and cocoa.
Boil for one minute.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add vanilla and stir.
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: italian green beans
directions: Put ingredients in shaker. Shake this well and pour over beans. Chill well. Crisp fried bacon may also be added.

title: special cheese cake
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly with electric mixer.
Line spring-form pan with graham cracker crumbs, mixed with 1/4 pound melted butter.
Pour cheese mixture into crust.
Bake for 20 minutes in 375° oven.
Remove from oven.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together except cake mix, oleo and nuts. Put pumpkin mixture into ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle the dry cake mix over mixture in cake pan.
Pour the melted oleo over top of cake mix and sprinkle the nuts on top of this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, no longer.
Cool.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.
Can omit ginger or nutmeg.

title: hummus
directions: Drain garbanzos but reserve liquid. Put garbanzos, oil, garlic and lemon juice in blender or food processor and blend. Gradually add about 1/2 of liquid and blend until smooth. Serve with pita bread.

title: pork chop and mushroom casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops in the oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Add soup and water.
Heat.
Pour mixture and pork chops into casserole dish.
Add potatoes and carrots.
Season to taste.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
This works great in an electric skillet.

title: garlic crackers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well, then add crackers.
Continue to stir every 30 minutes for 2 hours.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix soups and mayonnaise together.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan. First the broccoli, then second the chicken, then third the soup mixture.
Combine dry stuffing and grated cheese and sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until broccoli is cooked.
Serves 10 to 12.
Enjoy.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk and bananas.
Beat 3 minutes. Fold in nuts. Grease and flour 3 cake pans.
Put even amount of batter in each pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and sprinkle 1/2 in bottom of rectangular dish.
Set aside.
Mix pudding according to package.
Set aside. Beat together cream cheese, confectioners sugar and margarine. Then add to pudding mixture.
Stir in Dream Whip.
Spread mixture over the Oreos in the dish.
Then sprinkle remaining Oreos on top of mixture.
Serve cold.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add other ingredients and mix. Pour into mold.
Chill.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
If mold is a ring, fill center with cottage cheese with pineapple in it.
Very pretty.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix hamburger, water, rice, onion, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape into balls (approximately 12).
Mix sauce and water, pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.
Bake an additional 15 minutes uncovered.

title: strawberry glazed pie
directions: Wash strawberries and remove caps. Add powdered sugar to 3 cup of berries.
Let stand 1 hour.
Crush the remaining cup of berries.
Cook with water 2 minutes.
Press through a sieve.
Mix cornstarch and granulated sugar.
Stir into berry juice.
Cook gently until clear, stirring constantly, about 20 minutes.
Fill baked 8-inch pie shell with berries.
Cover with hot strawberry sauce.
Cool.

title: fish
directions: Spray dish with vegetable oil.
Lay fish fillets in dish; cover with salad dressing and horseradish sauce.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and pat of butter.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, uncovered.

title: pinwheel fruit cobbler
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves; set aside.
Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish in a 350° oven.
Set aside.
Cut shortening into flour.
Add milk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly for 4 to 5 times.
Roll into a 12 x 9-inch rectangle.
Spread sliced fruit over dough.
Roll up jellyroll fashion, beginning with long side.
Cut dough into 12 (1-inch) slices.
Place slices in butter.
Pour syrup over slices; bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until golden.

title: ham-and-corn chowder
directions: Saute ham, celery and onion in butter in a Dutch oven.
Stir in the next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix together all ingredients in large casserole dish, except onion rings.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven, top with onion rings and bake until onion rings are golden brown.

title: cool raspberry soup
directions: In a blender, puree raspberries, water and wine if desired. Transfer to a large saucepan.
Add the cran-raspberry juice, sugar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring just to a boil over medium heat.
Remove from the heat; strain and allow to cool.
Whisk in lemon juice and yogurt.
Refrigerate.
To serve, pour into small bowls and top with a dollop of sour cream.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cocoa-banana muffinettes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 30 miniature cups with paper cups or spray bottoms only with no stick cooking spray.
Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Add combined bananas, milk, margarine, egg whites and vanilla.
Fill prepared cups almost full.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Let muffins stand a few minutes.
Remove from pan, cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: bacon potato puff
directions: Cook bacon, until crisp & drain on paper towels and crumble. Reserve 2 Tbsp. of crumbled bacon.
In mixing bowl beat egg yolks until light about 2 minutes.
Beat in onion, mustard, and pepper. Set aside.
Place potatoes in bowl and fold in egg yolk mixture. Fold cheese, parsley and bacon into potato mix.
Beat egg whites until stiff, fold into potato mix.
Pour into a greased 1 qt. baking dish.
Sprinkle with reserved bacon.
Bake uncovered, at 325 degrees 45-50 minutes.
Until set and edges are golden brown. Serve warm.

title: pizza bread
directions: Beat eggs and add Parmesan cheese.
This will be used to baste the crust.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the ice cubes; stir until jello starts to gel.
Add the Cool Whip (use wire whip or spoon).
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: orange nut loaf
directions: Sift flour with salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add nut meats. Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients.
Stir (do not beat!) until just mixed.
Turn into loaf pan (4 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch pan).
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 cup canned milk, Bisquick and vanilla together and pour over melted oleo in pan.
Drain peaches and pour over batter.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over peaches, followed by 1 cup canned milk.
Sprinkle cinnamon over top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: pumpkin, banana or squash cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Dump remaining ingredients in and mix well.
Bake at 300° to 350°.
Makes 3 or 4 layers.

title: shrimp in chinese lobster sauce
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Butterfry shrimp by slicing them down the length of the back, stopping just above the tail.
Rinse with cold water; blot dry.
Cover the black beans with lukewarm water; let soak for 5 minutes and drain.
Combine with minced garlic and ginger; gently crush into a paste.
Mix in the wine and set aside.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the ingredients and put in a small loaf pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: european chocolate cake
directions: Grate or shave the chocolate so that it will melt uniformly. Melt butter until fully melted and very hot, then stir in the chocolate and continue to stir until the chocolate is melted. Whisk sugar and egg yolks together until light and then whisk into the chocolate/butter mixture until smooth.
Then whisk in flours and continue to whisk until batter is smooth.
Beat egg whites until they hold a stiff peak.
Briskly stir 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of beaten egg white into your chocolate mixture, then fold in remaining.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 9-inch Bundt pan.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix crumbs and margarine.
Put 1/2 on bottom of 13 X 9 inch glass dish.
Mix cream cheese and milk until smooth, add cool whip and sugar.
Put 1/2 on top of crackers.
Spread cherries on top, add remaining cool whip mixture on top of cherries.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Keep refrigerated.

title: macaroni and cheese #5
directions: Cook
macaroni;
drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 450° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: quick chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: moist molasses cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter to look like crumbs.
Keep 1 cup for topping.
Add molasses, water and baking soda to rest of mix. Pour into pan.
Sprinkle topping over the top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: spiced chicken and vegetables
directions: Mix together garlic salt, ginger, minced garlic, pepper and soy sauce.
Add chicken and marinate approximately 20 minutes.
Use 3 tablespoons oil to cook meat.
Then take meat out of oil and add more oil for cooking broccoli, salt, mushrooms and onion.
Add broccoli and salt first and then mushrooms and onions.
Add all together with chicken.
Serve over rice.

title: cereal-peanut bars
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and salt in saucepan; bring to a full boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla, cereals and chocolate chips.
Press into a buttered 9
x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut in small bars or squares.
(For easy serving, store in refrigerator.)
Makes about 2 dozen pieces. (Tastes almost like a candy bar.)

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine onion, squash and soup. Heat. Layer squash, cheese and crackers in a baking dish. Sprinkle crackers on top. Melt margarine and drizzle over crackers. Bake at 350° until browned.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Add soups, 1 1/2 cups hot water, rice and soy sauce; simmer 30 minutes.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; sprinkle with chow mein noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: diet soup
directions: Mix and cook until done.
Can eat all you want.

title: easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat the eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix (dry), cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.
Prepare pie filling as directed on package for pie.
Let stand about 5 minutes, or until thickened.
Spread over cake.
Store cake in refrigerator.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix together squash, onions and salt.
Place in pan and add 2 quarts ice.
Let stand 3 hours; drain and wash in cold water. Combine remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and add squash. Let come to boil again.
Put in jars and seal.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix and flour.
Add Jell-O, water and eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add berries and juice; beat one minute.
Add oil and beat 1 minute.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain and run cold water over it.
Drain cold spaghetti well.
Toss all ingredients (except the Italian dressing and the salad seasoning) together.
Pour Italian dressing and salad seasoning on mixture. Sprinkle with some Parmesan cheese.
Toss all together.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: spinach salad
directions: Clean and tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Add bacon, eggs and mushrooms.
Mix together oil, sugar, catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and onion and pour this dressing over salad when ready to serve.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl of electric mixer, beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until well mixed.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and and can juice, flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking powder.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into two greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° one hour or until bread tests done.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: easy deep dish pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet.
Mix Bisquick and water until soft dough forms.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured surface.
Knead 20 times.
Pat dough onto cookie sheet and up the sides of the pan with floured hands.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, remove skin and bones; set aside.

Mix chicken soup and mushroom soup together by directions on can; set aside. Melt margarine and toss in stuffing mix until butter is absorbed. In a baking dish, make a layer of 1/3 of the stuffing mix, a layer of 1/2 of the soup mixture, all of the chicken, 1/3 of the stuffing mixture in the next layer, the last half of the soup mixture and finally the last of the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in glass dish.

title: easy cheddar fondue on propane stove(method:  skillet)
directions: Mix the cream, wine (optional), Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard, pepper and mayonnaise together.
Beat with a whisk until the mixture is creamy and well blended.
Place in a fondue pot or pot over low heat; do not boil.
Immediately add the Cheddar cheese; stir to mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the cheese has melted and blended with the other ingredients.
Cook for a few minutes longer.
Makes 2 3/4 cups. Serve with bite size pieces of Italian or French bread.

title: atlanta chess pie
directions: Melt butter; add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in cornmeal, vinegar and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into unbaked shell and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked dressing casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix with stuffing, using all seasonings.
Put into greased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix the soups and water together and pour over stuffing mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Sift flour and spices together.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend 2 teaspoons vanilla into applesauce.
Add soda to applesauce.
Combine with batter mixture.
Batter will be stiff.
Fill greased muffin tins and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Yields about 85 muffins.

title: chili con carne
directions: In large skillet, brown meat; stir in onion soup mix, chili powder, kidney beans and tomatoes.
You may also add 1 cup of water if needed.
Simmer, covered for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bread
directions: Soften yeast and dissolve with 1 teaspoon of sugar in the water (lukewarm).
Add milk that is cool to lukewarm; add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour to make soft dough.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk oil, yeast cake and warm water.
Stir until blended.
Roll out.
Put melted butter, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Knead until dough becomes smooth and elastic; no longer than 5 to 10 minutes!
Place in greased bowl, grease top of dough and cover with wax paper; let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled (1 to 1 1/2 hours); punch down and form into rolls of desired shape.
Place in greased pan and let rise until doubled (30 to 40 minutes).
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili in crock-pot
directions: Cut into 1/2 inch cubes, place meat in crock-pot and stir in tomato paste to completely coat meat.
Add the remaining ingredients and stir to blend.
Do not add any additional liquid. Cover and cook for 12 hours on low heat.
Yield:
4 servings. Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 34 g, fat 24 g, calories 414.

title: lamb tangine
directions: Salt and pepper the meat.
Heat 3 tablespoons olive oil in pan and brown the meat.
Add onion, garlic and pepper and saute until onion is brown.
Add cinnamon, cumin, dates and apricots.
Cover meat with water until meat is tender and broth is thickened, approximately 25 minutes.
You may use chicken stock in place of water for a richer stew.
Garnish with remaining slivered almonds and with chopped cilantro.
Serve over rice.

title: pecos pasta
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add chili, corn, salt and pepper.
Simmer on low heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in cooked macaroni and top with shredded cheese.
Cover and heat on low for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; cool and thicken.
Beat cheese spread and mayonnaise.
Add Jell-O and cream.
Add remaining ingredients. Grease mold with a little mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.

title: hash brown breakfast bake
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread hash browns over melted margarine.
Slightly beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and browned sausage.
Pour mixture of eggs, milk, seasoning, cheese and sausage over the hash browns.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg sandwich filling
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and all other ingredients.
Cook in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Stir well while cooking.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Season to individual taste.
Drain meat before adding to sauce.
Let simmer for about 3 to 4 hours, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: seven layered salad
directions: Layer as listed except mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese.
Spread on top.
Cover tightly and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: barbecue marinade
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Marinate the chicken, then cook on a grill.
After removing from grill, pour lemon juice over the chicken.

title: christmas salad
directions: Use 1/3 less liquid for mixing jello.
Use some juice from fruits.
Put jello in shallow pans to jell.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Place apples in well-greased 10-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream together butter or margarine and remaining 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and mix with creamed mixture.
Spread over fruit.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve hot or cold with thin custard sauce or whipped cream.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Don't mix until ready to serve.
Can make 24 hours ahead of time.
Refrigerate.

title: irene's green bean casserole
directions: In a long casserole dish layer the ingredients starting with green beans and ending with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger. Add tomato sauce, V-8 and sauce mix.
Simmer 20 minutes. Layer meat sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese; end with meat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (covered with foil).
Remove foil the last 20 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes. Serve and enjoy.

title: inside out ravioli
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in tablespoon of vegetable oil. Stir in water, sauce and paste. Simmer 10 minutes. Mix cooked macaroni with cheese, bread crumbs, eggs and 1/2 cup vegetable oil. Spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Top with meat sauce and add extras (pepperoni, mushrooms, green peppers). Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes. Cut into squares and serve.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes 25 minutes in salted water.
Drain.
Peel and slice potatoes.
In a large skillet, fry bacon crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened. Stir in bacon and potatoes.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add hard-boiled eggs and toss.
Makes 7 servings.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Crumble cooked cornbread.
Pour broth from cooked chicken over bread.
Add other ingredients; stir well.
If too dry, add small amount of milk.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: tuna salad
directions: In large bowl,	stir together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss
lightly
to coat.
Cover tightly and chill.
This is nice to serve on lettuce.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, stirring well.
Spread evenly over popped corn.
Spread coated corn in large greased pan and bake at 250° for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Empty up while still warm.
Break apart and store in airtight container.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll in ball.
Roll in crushed pecans.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and Carnation evaporated milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips until well melted.
Add Kraft Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: quickie pie
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
It will become a thin batter. Melt 1 stick of butter in a 9 x 14 pan.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Don't mix - just pour.
Choose your fruit.
If fresh, add enough sugar to your taste and cook 15 minutes slowly.
Pour fruit (and juice) on top of butter and batter.
If canned fruit, pour entire can (fruit & juice) on top of the butter and batter.
Do not stir or mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 - 30 minutes (until brown).
Delicious and so easy and quick.

title: french country beef stew
directions: Combine meat and flour in plastic bag; toss to coat evenly. In 6-quart pot, brown meat in oil.
Salt and pepper to taste, if desired.
Add remaining ingredients, except mustard.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until beef is tender.
Blend in mustard.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with warm crusty French bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Heat
sugar,
butter
and
milk until boiling; boil one minute.
Take off the heat and add the salt and vanilla.
Stir and add the oats, peanut butter and cocoa.
Stir and drop onto wax paper and wait until stiff.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 9x13 pan with cooking oil.
Distribute croutons evenly over bottom of pan.
Mix eggs, milk, cheese and choice of meat and Rotel tomatoes together.
Blend well with fork and pour into pan. Cover with cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven in the morning to 350°. Bake 30-45 minutes or until knife inserted in center of egg casserole comes out clean.
Let set 10 minutes and serve with your favorite salsa.

title: walnut pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°. In mixing bowl, combine pumpkin, sweetened condensed milk, eggs, 3/4 teaspoon cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg
and salt. Mix well. Turn into pie crust. Bake about 15 minutes. Remove pie. Reduce oven to 350°.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Shape into a ball and roll in 1 cup pecans.
May have to chill before shaping into a ball.
Keep refrigerated.

title: quick quick snack bars
directions: In a large saucepan, combine honey peanut butter, and powdered milk. Cool and stir over low heat until blended. Remove from heat and stir in cereal. Press into an 8 inch square baking dish that has been coated with non stick spray. Let stand until set. Cut into bars. Yield about 1 dozen.

title: black walnut pudding
directions: Combine Cool Whip, condensed milk and sweet milk; mix together for 5 minutes.
Add pudding.
Use large bowl and layer with wafers, then layer walnuts, layer of milk and pudding mixture.
Repeat vanilla wafers, walnuts, pudding and milk.
Mixture will all be used, then top with Cool Whip.
Chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Day before, cook chicken breasts, cool and cut into bite-size cubes.
Toss in French dressing and marinate overnight.
Add celery and mayonnaise to taste to make a chicken salad.
If desired, add nuts.
Spread salad in baking dish and spread cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until hot.
Put can of French fried onions on top and bake another 5 minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix and shape into 1-inch balls.
Fry or broil.
Drain.

title: robin's hearty chicken soup
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover until almost done.
Add all remaining ingredients; cook until soup starts to thicken and chicken is cooked, stirring occasionally.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes (like French fries).
Melt margarine in iron skillet.
Add potatoes, sugar and water.
Cover and cook until potatoes are soft.
Remove lid and cook until syrup is thick.

title: chocolate banana frosting
directions: Melt and cool chocolate.
Cream together butter and powdered sugar.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Add cooled chocolate, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Add more milk, a few drops at a time, if frosting is too thick.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except butter and mix well.
Shape meat into balls.
Melt butter in large frying pan.
Brown slowly in butter over low heat.
Place meatballs in hot cooked sauce. Cover and cook an additional 30 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: chimichangas with beef and beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain excess grease; add onion, pepper and corn.
Cook for 5 minutes. Stir in taco sauce and season with chili powder, garlic salt and cumin.
Stir until blended.
Cook until heated thoroughly.
Spread a thin layer of beans onto each of the 10 tortillas.
Spoon the beef mixture down the center and top with shredded cheese.
Fold sides in and roll up.
Place seam side down on a lightly greased pan.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Serve with shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes and a dollop of sour cream.

title: all round dinner
directions: Wash pork chops.
Add salt and pepper.
Dip in flour.
Let brown on both sides in hot grease (1 minute).
Arrange in roaster. Add to each chop 1 tablespoon uncooked rice, 1 slice of onion, 1 slice of peeled tomato and 1 ring of bell pepper.
Put one small piece of butter in the pepper ring.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Carefully add hot water to cover rice.
Cover and cook one hour.

title: spiced apple simmer
directions: In 5 quart Dutch oven, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer 20 minutes. Remove spices and discard.
Serve hot.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add the beaten egg yolks, crushed pineapple and nuts.
Beat the 2 egg whites until stiff; fold into the other mixture.
Spread between butter wafers, using 4 wafers and leaving top one dry.
Frost ball with whipped cream.
(One box of cookies makes 12 snowballs.) The half pint of whipped cream will not quite cover the 12 balls.
Let stand 4 hours in the refrigerator.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Saute onions, peppers, garlic, mushrooms and celery.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 35 to 45 minutes.
Add chicken after 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: lemon apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in a tube pan.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt together the chocolate, butter or margarine and water. Meanwhile, in a large bowl, measure and mix together flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
To this mixture, add eggs, vanilla and melted chocolate and butter mixture.
Beat until blended.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done in center.

title: tortilla wheels
directions: Mix and spread on tortilla shells.
Roll and cut into bite size pieces.
Serve with salsa.

title: inexpensive fruitcake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients and cloves, if used, in a saucepan. Bring to boil for 3 minutes. Cool. Then add a mixture of soda, salt and water. Sift together flour and baking powder and blend into cake. Grease or use Pam and spray the little size pans, 3 of them, or you can use big loaf pan, also. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: hamburger heaven
directions: Brown meat.
Season to taste.
Sprinkle noodles over meat. Add in order the onions, green pepper, celery and tomatoes.
Cook for 25 to 30 minutes (simmer).
Place in a 13 x 9-inch ovenware dish.
Sprinkle cheese and olives on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Grease 9 x 13 glass pan.

title: f d r delight
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg, sugar and flour until light and fluffy.
Stir in remaining ingredients with egg mixture.
Bake in greased oblong dish 30 to 35 minutes.
Great served hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.
Line bottom of long Pyrex dish with crumbs.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread out on top of crumbs.
Top with reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken.
Brown rice and onion in 1 tablespoon butter. Spread rice in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.

title: smoked salmon spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into serving bowl; cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle with parsley just before serving.
Serve with Melba rounds.
Yields 2 cups (about 38 calories per tablespoon).

title: scotch broth
directions: Trim fat from meat and cut into small pieces.
Put in pot with 8 cups cold water.
Bring to a boil and stir in barley.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat and barley are tender, adding more water if needed.
Remove meat from bones.
Cool soup and skim off fat.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add vegetables. Cook over low heat, stirring often, for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add meat and vegetables to soup.
Cook another 10 minutes and serve hot.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Lay rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Seal seams and bake per directions.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayo, dressing mix and onions.
Spread this mixture over top of rolls.
Then top with chopped veggies (press in slightly).
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight.
Cut in squares.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in a Dutch oven or casserole.
Add to the pork chops the Kitchen Bouquet and water.
Top chops with rice, then onions, then tomatoes.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Salt may be added after rice, if desired.

title: eggplant creole
directions: Rinse eggplant.
Peel and slice almost all the way through (accordion style).
Place eggplant in a 2-quart saucepan.
Place onion and bell pepper slices between eggplant slices.
Combine celery, tomatoes, salt, peppers, oil and vinegar; pour over eggplant.
Cook, covered, over medium heat until eggplant is tender (about 20 minutes).
Place in serving dish; sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Garnish with cherries.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Cut raw bacon in half; wrap around pineapple and water chestnuts.
Pierce with a toothpick.
Microwave on High for 7 minutes.

title: hot butter drink
directions: Combine in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Cook slow for 10 minutes.
Cool and store in freezer container.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: This will make a crumbly mixture.
Place on top of sweet potato mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hershey bar dessert
directions: Melt in double boiler the marshmallows in the milk; cool and add Hershey bars, breaking them into pieces.
Stir until melted. Cool.
Add 1 cup of whipped cream and pour into unbaked pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: abby's gourmet rice pudding(simply delicious)
directions: In top of double boiler, combine rice, boiling water and salt. Cook over medium heat about 40 minutes or until rice is tender. Do not drain.
Stir in condensed milk and butter.
Cook, stirring frequently, until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add raisins (which have been plumped up in hot water and then drained before adding).
Add vanilla.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chinese cabbage
directions: Toast almonds and sesame seed in oven at 350° for 15 minutes. Stir twice.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, pepper and chicken flavor seasoning packet from soup.
Put on cabbage.
Add other ingredients just before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Set aside. Combine all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (round or oblong).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
May also be baked in greased and floured bread tins, or as cupcakes.

title: apricot fudge
directions: Boil sugar, sour cream and oleo 7 minutes.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch square buttered dish or pan and cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Blend in bananas, eggs, vanilla extract, flour, baking soda
and salt. Add the banana mixture, alternating with buttermilk and mix thoroughly after each addition.
Add nuts.
Mix.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dream pie(this makes two pies)
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and cherries.
Be sure you have two cups.
Add sugar and flour to juice.
Boil until thick.
Add dry jello to hot mixture.
Add fruit and nuts (and red food color, if needed).
Chill.
Then add bananas.
Pour in baked pie crust and chill until firm.
Serve with whipped cream or topping.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Add soup, green beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Now put into casserole and cover with mashed potatoes. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Start layering with lettuce, following with remaining ingredients in the order given.
Top with the Hidden Valley dressing.
May be fixed the night before and put in icebox.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Peel green from watermelon rinds; soak in 4 quarts of water and salt for 24 hours.
Drain.
Cover melon slices with boiling water and boil 1 1/2 hours.
Drain and put melon into ice water until thoroughly chilled.
Drain.

title: ham 'n swiss broccoli quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine half and half, eggs, mustard and pepper; set aside.
Layer ham, cheese, broccoli and onion in crust.
Pour egg mixture over the other ingredients in crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted in center.
Cool for 5 to 7 minutes and serve.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Core apples and slit skin around the middle of each.
Place apples in small dishes.
Place butter in a 1-cup glass measure and cook for 30 seconds at 1/2 power.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Cover each dish with plastic wrap and cook on High power 4 to 5 minutes.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Put oil, melted chocolate and sugar in bowl and beat it together.
Add egg 1 at a time and beat well.
Add vanilla.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in.
Beat it good (may be stiff, okay).
Cover it over and put in refrigerator for another day.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten egg.
Stir baking into heated applesauce and add alternately with with dry ingredients. Add vanilla last.
Bake in greased muffin tins until light brown. Bake at 350 degrees 15 to 20 minutes.

title: lemony lemonade syrup base
directions: In covered jar, combine lemon peel, sugar and boiling water; cover and shake until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon juice, store tightly covered in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 2 2/3 cups syrup base, enough for 8 to 10 servings.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, dry onion soup mix and green pepper. Blend thoroughly and add 1/2 can Hunt's spaghetti sauce and 1 cup plain bread crumbs. Mix well and if more bread crumbs are needed, add more to desired consistency. Form meat mixture into loaf shape. Spray glass baking dish with Pam and place loaf in dish. Mix remaining Hunt's sauce and 1/2 cup ketchup in bowl. Spread over meat loaf before baking. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes. Slice and serve!

title: good 'n quick coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt and half the flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg, shortening, vanilla and remainder
of flour.
Drop by spoonfuls over bottom of greased pan.
Cover
and
let rise until doubled in bulk. Bake in 375° oven
until
golden
brown.
Remove
from
oven.
Mix together remaining
ingredients
of
powdered sugar, cream, coconut and pecans.
Spread topping on top of hot cake immediately.

title: cauliflower parmesan
directions: Cook cauliflower for 10 minutes, or until tender.
Heat butter and stir in bread crumbs.
Remove from heat.
Place cauliflower in small baking dish.
Pour buttered bread crumbs over and sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in broiler for 1 minute.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs on medium speed. Add sugar and beat until light.
Add margarine and beat.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add these to batter. Beat on low speed.
Fold in pecans.
