Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until done. Cover marshmallows and return to oven for 1 minute.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) and heat in large skillet on stove.
Place layer of tortillas, sauce and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir and keep at room temperature for 24 hours.
Refrigerate until next feeding.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain.
Add soup, milk, wine, butter and pepper.
Heat through.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, rice, water, green pepper, chili powder, salt and garlic powder.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Sprinkle with corn chips.

title: zesty bacon dip
directions: Mix cottage cheese and cream cheese in a bowl.
Stir in bacon, horseradish, scallions, parsley and pimento.
Chill for 1 hour. Serve with vegetables or crackers.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream, cream cheese and 1 package taco seasoning. Spread into dish with sides.
Warm refried beans and spread next. Brown ground beef and drain grease.
Spread on top of refried beans.
Layer tomatoes, lettuce and cheese. Can put lettuce and tomatoes to side and let it be added later.
Serve with bag of tortilla chips for dipping.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Cook raisins and dates together in apple juice.
Beat egg; add milk.
Melt oleo in cooked raisin and date mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Use 1 1/2 or 2-quart buttered casserole.
Layer half the beans, water chestnuts, mushrooms and onion.
Cover with half the soups and cheese.
Repeat layers, topping with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Melt butter and chocolate in saucepan over low heat.
Remove and stir in remaining ingredients. Beat well. Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.
Can be iced with chocolate bars.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing, soup mix and preserves.
Pour over chicken in a large, shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste once or twice with pan drippings. Serve hot with plain rice and sweet and sour sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: ham rolls
directions: Combine ingredients, spread on thin sliced ham, roll and fasten with cocktail picks.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: yellow cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions and bake.
Hold 1 cup batter; mix with remaining ingredients.
Cook until thick and pour over cake.

title: play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook over medium heat until it forms a ball.
Pour out and knead it well.
Keep it in covered container or plastic bag.
To color, use food coloring before cooking.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until firm.

title: crispy ham balls
directions: Mix potatoes, ham and onion flakes and roll into balls.
Roll balls in butter and then in corn flakes.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serve with cheese sauce.

title: sour cream pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in layers or sheet cake.
In saucepan, add pineapple, cornstarch and sugar.
Cook until thickens.
Add lemon juice, margarine and vanilla.
Allow filling to cool.
Add pint of sour cream.
After cake is cool, spread filling between layers and on top of cake.
Use all the filling.
Refrigerate after one day.

title: roquefort and shrimp stuffed sole
directions: Mix ingredients for the filling and refrigerate for 30 minutes to firm up.

title: salmon dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours before serving.
May be used with your favorite snack crackers or chips.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well. Set aside and let cool.
Mix all other ingredients and add broccoli.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Turn oven off and leave in for 5 more minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer in order listed.
Stir when ready to serve.

title: banana-spice pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing until fairly smooth. Cook the same as regular pancakes. Serve with Honey-Butter.

title: brunch special
directions: Arrange 6 slices of bread (crusts trimmed) in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with 6 slices cheese and 6 more slices of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sandwiches.
Let stand 1 hour or more.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° oven until brown and puffy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples and water in a 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt into a bowl.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over the apples. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until the apples are tender.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in casserole for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, until bubbly and hot. Serve with bread sticks, crackers, etc.

title: coconut squares
directions: Place butter in 9-inch round microproof baking dish (I use glass pie plate). Cook
on High 1 minute or until melted.
Stir in crumbs and sugar.
Pat mixture firmly and evenly in bottom of dish. Cook on High 2 minutes. Cool partially.
Mix coconut, milk and nuts. Spoon carefully over graham cracker crust. Cook on High 4 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once during cooking.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits.
Cook on High 1 minute. Spread melted chocolate evenly over coconut mixture.
(The chips will look solid but will really be melted.)
Cool and cut into 16 to 20 squares. These taste like Almond Joys.

title: greaseless chili
directions: Add salt to meat; then fry meat.
Pour off excess grease. Lightly coat meat with flour to absorb all grease.
Add chili powder and mix.
Add tomatoes, onion and kidney beans.
Add water and salsa or picante to chili.
Simmer for hours until done.
Stir periodically.
No grease on chili!

title: quick pear cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place pear halves, cut side up, in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with lemon juice, then with brown sugar. Pour 3 tablespoons of melted butter or margarine evenly over pear halves.
Cover and bake 20 minutes or until just tender.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oil; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture and beat well.
Stir in carrots, nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yums
directions: Generously grease jelly
roll
pan,
approximately 10 x 15-inch.
Line the pan
with
a single layer of soda crackers. (Fill pan completely.
If
necessary,
break
crackers in half for edges.)
Gently
boil
butter
and brown sugar 3 minutes. Pour over
crackers.
Bake
for	5 minutes in 350° oven. Cool slightly. Spread
chocolate chips over the top. Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Cut while warm. Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter cookies with a kiss
directions: Cream peanut butter, butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape dough into small balls and roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Kisses on top of each cookie.
Press down so cookie cracks.
Return to oven 2 to 5 minutes until golden brown.

title: pizza pasta pie
directions: Sprinkle wheat germ in baking dish; set aside.
Mix margarine into hot spaghetti with 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Mix well.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust. Use paper towel; squeeze excess liquid from spinach.
Spread spinach over pasta crust.
Drain cottage cheese.

title: chewy pecan pie bars
directions: Grease a
1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Preheat oven to
In
medium
bowl
with fork, mix baking powder, 1 1/2 cups flour and
cup packed brown sugar.
With pastry blender or 2 knives
used scissor-fashion, cut butter or margarine
into flour mixture
until
mixture
resembles
very
fine crumbs.
Pat mixture firmly and evenly into prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In a large
bowl
with mixer at medium speed, beat eggs until foamy. Beat in
corn syrup, vanilla, 1/2 cup packed brown sugar and 1/2 cup
flour
until
well
blended.
Pour egg mixture over partially baked layer; sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 55 minutes longer or until
set.
Cool
in pan.
Cut into bars. Store in refrigerator. Makes 35 bars.

title: omaha style potatoes
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Saute onions in stick of butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs, pimento, parsley or crumbled bacon.
Cover and bake 1 hour. Uncover and bake 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: mae johnson pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers thin; pack in jar.
Make liquid of the remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers cold and seal.

title: southern applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add applesauce mixed with soda.
Sift flour and measure 4 cups.
Add to mixture.
Stir well. Bake in appropriate size sheet cake pan at 275° for approximately 55 to 60 minutes.

title: one pan banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a loaf pan.
With a wooden spoon, mix all the ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Pour the batter into the greased pan.
Bake for 55 minutes or until done.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 350°.
In medium bowl , beat eggs slightly.
Blend in sugar, corn syrup, butter and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Pour into frozen pie crust.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted between edge and center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Use old bread or biscuits.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Place chicken in a large kettle.
Add 2 quarts of water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until chicken is tender.
Take chicken from broth (reserve broth).
Remove chicken from bone; cut in pieces.
Cook spaghetti in broth until tender; drain well. Blend soup and milk in saucepan.
Add chicken, pimento and mushrooms; heat thoroughly.
Layer spaghetti, chicken mixture and Cheddar cheese in casserole dish.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Top with Parmesan cheese and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: raisin apple coffee cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening together thoroughly.
Add milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange thinly sliced apples in fancy designs on top of batter.
Press in slightly.
Sprinkle top with 1 teaspoon cinnamon, mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.
Test with toothpick.
Serve warm.
(Freezes well and warms in microwave.)

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Measure 2 cups cranberries, then grind.
Combine cranberries, sugar and marshmallows.
Cover and chill overnight, then add apples, nuts, salt and fold in Cool Whip.

title: storybook salad
directions: Layer spinach, mushrooms, carrots, cucumber, onion and orange slices in 2 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Top with dressing.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage to crumble.
Drain off most of grease.
Cook green onions, green pepper and celery.
Add chicken noodle soup mix, water, rice and water chestnuts.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered, at 350°.
This dish may be frozen.

title: bessie's caramel pie
directions: Combine in a large saucepan the sugar, flour and cornstarch. Add to this the butter, milk and slightly beaten yolks of eggs. Add salt and place over medium heat. Place 1/2 cup of sugar in a heavy skillet over medium heat. Stir the first mixture at frequent intervals while you keep an eye on sugar in skillet. As soon as the custard mixture begins to cook slightly, stir constantly until it reaches a rolling boil. By this time, the sugar in the skillet should have begun to melt. When almost all of it has melted, stir well. It should be caramelized and bubbly all over. As soon as this stage is reached, add the first mixture, stirring constantly. Continue cooking until it is smooth creamy and thickened. Remove from the heat.

title: orange gumdrop
directions: Beat eggs with water until foamy.
Gradually add sugar and salt; beat until light and fluffy.
Thoroughly mix candy (orange slices), coconut, walnuts and flour; stir into egg mixture. Spread on greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done in middle and cut into squares.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: instant brunch
directions: Mix cheese, ham and walnuts.
Spread on toasted waffle.
Cover with second waffle.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix above ingredients well.
Allow to stand about 30 minutes before serving.

title: "chess cake"
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and egg and smooth in 13 x 9 pan, sprayed.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Then beat cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sorghum syrup cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix milk, egg, syrup and melted shortening.
Mix well with dry ingredients and pour into a square baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: vegetarian potato-cheese soup(serves 6)
directions: In large soup pot, saute onions and garlic in butter until onions are translucent.
Add potatoes and carrots; saute for 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Add stock and dill.
Simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Puree the vegetables with the cream cheese and milk in blender or food processor.
Return the soup to soup pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in Cheddar cheese and reheat gently.

title: loverly coconut cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add to creamed mixture: flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla. Fold in uncooked oatmeal, shredded coconut and nuts of your choice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, 1/2 stick margarine and milk together.
Melt 1/2 stick of margarine in pan or dish.
Pour batter over melted margarine or butter.
Pour peaches on top of batter and cup of sweetened water to make enough juice.
Bake at 350° until brown. Crust will rise as it bakes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo; add cream-style corn and whole kernel corn.
Stir in beaten eggs and sour cream dip, then add corn bread mix.
Bake in an 8-inch square casserole dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or just until firm in center.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: strawberry jello dessert-salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and pack tightly in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the next 3 ingredients until creamy.
Spread on top of the cooled crust. Combine jello and water.
Add strawberries.
When it starts to jell (slightly thickened), pour over top of cheese, then refrigerate.
Best if made the day before serving.

title: fettuccine alfredo(quick, easy and good!)
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
While fettuccine cooks, combine 1 cup of the heavy cream, butter, pepper and nutmeg in a pot large enough to hold pasta and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add fettuccine, tossing to coat. Add remaining heavy cream and 3/4 cup of the cheese.
Toss again and serve with remaining cheese sprinkled on top.
Serves 6.

title: tangy pork chops
directions: Wash potatoes and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover the potatoes with the sauerkraut.
Arrange the pork chops on the sauerkraut.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chinese tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except noodles, in ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with noodles.
Bake, uncovered, until contents are bubbly and noodles golden brown, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with hot rolls and salad.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in jars.
Use as needed, 2 to 3 teaspoons per cup hot water.

title: mexican dip
directions: Blend over low heat to melt cheese.
Serve warm with chips.

title: tabboulen salad
directions: Place bulgar and water in large bowl and let soak at least 1 hour; drain.
Add remaining ingredients except oil; toss.
Just before serving, stir in oil.
Serve on Romaine lettuce.
Tastes better the second day.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugars; beat in eggs and add vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats and raisins; form into small balls.
Place about 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together well.
Next, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: snow ice cream
directions: Beat egg until it is foamy.
Add sugar and continue beating. Pour in milk and vanilla.
Go out and get large bowl of clean, fresh snow.
Add large spoonfuls to egg mixture.
Keep stirring until thick.
Eat and enjoy.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
When cake gets done, punch holes and pour mixture over cake.
Let cake get cold.
Take Cool Whip and spread on cake; top with coconut.

title: lo-cal reubens
directions: Combine sauerkraut and dressing in a bowl and mix well.
Top each slice of toast with half the corned beef, one cheese product and 1/2 cup of the sauerkraut mixture.
Broil until hot.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine all.
Place in a greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: fried apple slices
directions: Core apples, leaving peel on.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Mix egg, flour, 1/4 cup sugar and milk.
Heat oil (1/4-inch deep) in frying pan over medium heat.
Dip apple slices in batter.
Fry a few at a time until brown.
Turn over with spatula and brown on other side. Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar mixture while hot.
Makes 12 to 16 slices.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan or angel food pan (10 x 4-inch).
Beat all ingredients, except Glaze, on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes. Scrape bowl occasionally.
Spread in pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool.
Drizzle with Glaze.

title: whole wheat muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place whole wheat flour in a large mixing bowl, then sift all-purpose flour with sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Toss well into mix.
Beat egg with milk, oil and molasses until foamy.
Make a well in the center of the dry ingredients.
Pour in liquid all at once and stir lightly and quick to mix.
Batter should be lumpy.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Fill each cup 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes until lightly brown.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: In a bowl stir together soup, milk and onion soup.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the soup mixture.
Set aside.
Stir uncooked rice and thawed vegetables into remaining soup mixture.

title: strawberry bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Stir thawed strawberries, eggs and oil in a large bowl. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and nuts in another bowl.
Add dry ingredients to wet ones.
Pour into 2 bread pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: basic pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Beat egg yolks in heavy pan.
Add sugar and flour mixture, alternating with milk, into eggs until all is mixed.
Add butter and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add vanilla.

title: applesauce cookie
directions: Mix together sugar and Butter Buds; add baking soda to applesauce.
Add applesauce to Butter Buds mixture; blend well. Sift dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Add raisins and Grape-Nuts.
Chill dough 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Yields 9 to 10 dozen.

title: chocolate fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and extract.
Add eggs, one at a time. Blend in cooled chocolate.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together, alternately with water.
Add fruit and nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured 9-inch tube pan for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breasts; skin, debone and cut up into small chunks.
Put the chicken into a 13 x 9 pan.
Mix soup, broth, sour cream and mixed vegetables together and pour over chicken.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Add butter to hot macaroni. Then add soup, water, mayonnaise, onion and pimentos.
Stir this all together, then add cheese.
Cook at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: yogurt russian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl with a top.
Whisk until creamy and all is combined and smooth.
Cover; refrigerate.
It will keep for 3 or 4 days.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cream sugar, butter and egg.
Stir in orange juice.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture until combined real well.
Drain apricots well.
Add to batter with nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt in skillet the butter or oleo.
Sprinkle brown sugar over melted butter.
Arrange pineapple slices on top of brown sugar. Mix the next 8 ingredients in bowl.
Beat 2 minutes; add eggs and beat 2 more minutes.
Pour over sugar and pineapple slices in skillet.
Bake in oven at 250° or in an electric skillet lined with wax paper at 250°.

title: tourtiere(quebecois meat pie)
directions: Prepare pie crust, roll out top and bottom.
Press bottom crust into large deep pie plate.

title: pig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Combine condensed milk, pineapple, pecans, coconut, 1/2 container whipped topping and lemon juice.
Pour into crust and top with remaining whipped topping and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch and water to a boil.
Stir until clear and thick.
Add strawberry jello, stirring constantly.
Add strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cool. Top with whipped cream.
Yum.

title: carnival candy apples
directions: Butter cookie sheet generously.
Mix sugar, water, syrup and coloring in heavy saucepan.
Boil, without stirring, until reaching hard-crack stage.
Push sticks in apples through stem side.
Dip apples quickly in syrup, twirling until completely covered.
Stand on cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator until hardened.

title: double pleasure chicken and fresh vegetables
directions: Combine vegetables in 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon parsley, 2 teaspoons basil, salt and pepper. Pour chicken broth over vegetables.

title: raspberry fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in bowl and place on a large platter.
Surround with fresh fruits for dipping (strawberries, pineapple, cherries, bananas, apples, peaches, pears, etc.).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a well-greased pan until golden brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Heat pan; spray with Pam.
Add steak and cook until brown. Add vegetables.
Stir all other ingredients in and simmer for 30 minutes, until meat is tender.
If pan juices need thickening, add 2 tablespoons flour, mixed with 1/2 cup water.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 or 5 main dish servings.

title: gelatin slush
directions: Combine sugar, gelatin and water in 1-qt. Batter bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved. Add pineapple juice. Divide mixture evenly into 3 freezer safe containers. Freeze until firm. Remove from containers, grind and serve with a spoon.

title: oatmeal raisin bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, soda and spices and add to the mix.
Mix well.
Add oats, raisins, cranberries and nuts.
Bake in greased baking dish at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together the milk, egg and oil.
Add milk mixture to cornmeal mixture.
Stir only enough to mix.
(I bake this in a greased cast-iron skillet.) Bake at 425° (hot oven) until lightly browned.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend cream cheese until creamy.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove meat from bone and cut in small pieces. Cook spaghetti in 1-quart of broth.
Heat until well blended the soups and pimento.
Add to spaghetti; fold in chicken last.
Cook until thick.
Can cook on top of stove.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix well salmon, milk, salt, pepper, celery, cracker crumbs, lemon juice and egg.
Bake in greased dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: perfect turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag; place bag in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place onion and celery in bag.
Rinse, drain and pat turkey breast dry.
Brush with vegetable oil; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Place turkey breast in bag.
Close bag with nylon tie; make 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Insert meat thermometer through slit in bag into thickest part of turkey breast, but not touching bone.
Bake 1 3/4 to 2 3/4 hours or until meat thermometer registers 175°.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 5 to 10 servings.

title: pizza spins
directions: Brown meat and sausage; drain.
Spread cheese on top of meat mixture.
Add sauce and salt.
Spread mixture on cocktail bread. Bake 4 to 6 minutes in a 400° oven.
Makes 36 open-faced sandwiches.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and beat.
Add vanilla. Mix flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to batter and beat.
Add walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured square baking pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Divide chicken broth in half.
Add onions, bell peppers, garlic, comino, black pepper, salt and tomatoes.
Use enough cornstarch for desired consistency.
Clean chicken off the bones; cut up.
Soften corn tortillas with butter in frypan just enough to roll easily.
Roll chicken in tortillas. Top with lettuce, onion and avocado.
Spoon sauce on top and serve.

title: japanese fruit bars
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vinegar; mix well.
Stir in raisins, pecans, coconut, salt and water; set aside.

title: green chili stew
directions: Cut off excess fat from roast and cut into bite-size pieces. Brown in deep stew pot, leaving juices.
Add stewed tomatoes, chopping into small pieces.
Add green chilies (chopped).
Add bouillon cubes and cumin, starting with 1 tablespoon to taste. Add 2 to 3 tablespoons butter or margarine.

title: spinach or broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into Bundt Pan (grease and flour pan). Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Glaze.

title: skillet rice
directions: Place ground beef in large frying pan or skillet.
Brown, but don't cook fully.
Drain off fat.
Add 1/2 cup water and bring to a boil.
Add rice, slice onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Add tomatoes, white pepper and salt to taste.
Let simmer.

title: light pasta salad
directions: Mix dressing in large bowl until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper, if desired.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and celery in a large skillet.
Drain. Stir in soup and thyme.
Spoon meat mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart dish.
Spread potatoes evenly over meat mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bake 5 minutes until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: rosemary's cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Ready to serve.
Makes enough for about 6 people.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough and press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cover crust with meat mixture.
Top with processed cheese spread.
Continue to bake until cheese spread begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.

title: chocolate brownie cake
directions: Bring to a boil cocoa and margarine.
Add sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and spread on cool brownies.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In small saucepan over low heat, combine margarine, soup and cheese.
Stir until melted.
Arrange broccoli in baking dish and pour sauce over broccoli.
In large skillet, toast almonds and bread crumbs in additional melted margarine until crisp and lightly browned.
Sprinkle evenly over top and bake at 300° until bubbly.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk and cream to just ready to boil, over low to medium heat.
In small pan, put remaining ingredients, including oyster liquid.
Cook until edges start to curl on oysters.
Add to milk mix and serve immediately.

title: herbed pot roast
directions: Trim all visible fat from meat.
Coat a Dutch oven with vegetable cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Place roast in Dutch oven and brown on all sides.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine next 7 ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Add onion and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until roast is tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook until mushrooms are thoroughly heated.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove roast from cooking liquid.
Skim fat from liquid.
Yields 12 servings.

title: favorite christmas cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add dry ingredients, flour, salt and baking powder alternately with 1/2 cup whiskey.
Stir in white raisins and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Turn into well-greased and sugared Bundt or angel food pan.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for approximately 2 hours.
Cool, remove from pan.
Wrap cake in cheesecloth wet with additional whiskey.
Wrap in foil and store in tin, tightly covered.
Aging makes it better!

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cut up.
Mix onion, green pepper, pimento, celery and lemon juice and add to potatoes.
Add mayonnaise and salt, chill for an hour before serving.

title: country style pork chops
directions: Roll chops in seasoned flour.
Brown quickly on both sides in fat.
Remove from pan.
Add flour to hot grease; brown.
Add salt and water.
Stir until smooth.
Add chops to gravy.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put pineapple, cherries or strawberries in long cake pan. Spread dry cake mix over fruits.
Sprinkle nuts over.
Cut up stick of butter and place over cake.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes at 350°.

title: bread for christmas eve
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Set in warm place to rise.
Sift flour in deep bowl, add 2 cups warm water, 4 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and salad oil.
Knead well and set aside to rise.

title: nectar cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale and lime slices in large container. Mix in 2 cups cold water. Chill until serving time.
Add ginger ale. Serve over ice. Garnish glasses with lime slices.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Heat oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook over medium heat about 15 minutes until brown on both sides.

Remove chicken. Saute onion, garlic and green pepper just until tender. Combine remaining ingredients. Return chicken to skillet and pour sauce mixture over chicken. Cover and simmer slowly 40 minutes or until tender. Remove bay leaves. Serve with hot thin spaghetti and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot with milk and enough water to cover.
Cook and add butter.

title: simple lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredient well; form a dough.
Shape into meatball form or you may create a bow twist.
Bake at 350° on cookie sheets approximately 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until browned well.
In a large casserole bowl, mix beans, sugar, mustard, onion and bell pepper. Stir well, then add ground beef; mix well.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Wash 6 medium size potatoes, leaving peeling on (slice in half).
Melt 1/2 stick to 1 stick of butter in 9x13 baking dish. Sprinkle with Lawry's Seasoned Salt until bottom of pan is completely covered.
Place potatoes meat side down into butter and seasoned salt mixture.
Bake at 375 degrees until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and top with cheese and paprika.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sour cream nuggets
directions: Mix butter, sugar and eggs; stir in sour cream, vanilla and nuggets.
Combine dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture. Drop on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar supreme cheese cake
directions: Mix Zwieback crumbs with 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon grated lemon rind in small bowl.
Blend in melted butter.
Press evenly over bottom and sides of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Set pan in a 12-inch long piece of foil; fold foil up along side to catch any butter that may bubble out.
Chill while making filling.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Pour into crust and bake at 500° for 12 minutes.
Lower to 250° and bake for 2 hours or until firm on top.
Cool.
Garnish with canned or fresh fruit.
Cherries are great!

title: mimi's squash casserole
directions: In
a large covered pot, boil cut up squash and chopped onion until
tender.
Drain well in colander.
Return to pot. Add
eggs, Rice Krispies and salt and mix well.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking
dish;
dot
top with margarine.
Bake in 350° oven
about 30 minutes or until golden brown around edges and eggs are set. Serve hot.

title: ham & broccoli bake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch metal pan. Partially cook broccoli; drain well on paper towels. Cut off crusts and cube bread, spread in pan. Layer ham, then broccoli. Sprinkle onion, then cheese.
In large bowl, combine beaten eggs, milk, salt and mustard. Pour over bread. Cover, refrigerate 6 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 325°. Bake uncovered for 1 1/4 hours until inserted knife comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, then add eggs one at a time and blend in between each one.
Then add flour and flavoring.
Put in greased and floured pan and cook 55 minutes at 325°.

title: drying agent for flowers
directions: Mix ingredients equally in waterproof container.
Layer fresh flowers (wild or hybrid).
Leave undisturbed for about 6 weeks. Remove flour and dust off.
Many flowers will retain natural color if dried this way.

title: grandma's sponge cake
directions: Sift flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add cream of tartar.
Gradually beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until whites form stiff peaks.
In small bowl, combine egg yolks, water, vanilla and sifted dry ingredients. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Fold yolk mixture gently, but thoroughly, into beaten egg whites.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt the bacon fat in a heavy skillet.
Saute bacon and onion in the fat until bacon is crisp.
Add the potatoes, water and liquid from the oysters.
Cover skillet and cook until potatoes are done.
Add oysters and cream.
Simmer until oysters curl at the edges.
Season to taste.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each breast with a piece of bacon. Cover bottom of flat greased baking dish with chipped beef.
Mix soup and sour cream. Pour over all.
Refrigerate until ready to cook.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.
